msgctxt "Content/2871818096"
msgid ""
"After studying my scouts' reports, I have concluded that few tribes remain "
"who can successfully resist the New Legion's march. However, the island's "
"snowy tundras are a matter of concern. The dominant tribe in the region, the "
"Howling Wolves, are known to be fierce fighters. More importantly, a "
"prolonged invasion would prove nigh impossible in that weather.\n"
"\n"
"Yes, for now I shall avoid the frozen north. Instead I will annex the smaller "
"tribes, consolidate the New Legion's holdings and investigate the obelisks "
"with Rockwell. Perhaps their power can solve my northern conundrum.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/852400475"
msgid ""
"After studying the prism for all this time, I'm only certain of one thing - "
"if I insert it into my implant, something will change forever. Myself, "
"probably, but maybe not. Who's to say I'd even survive the experience? "
"Whatever the case, I think that's what it wants from me, and it wants it "
"urgently.\n"
"\n"
"And me? I still want answers, but I keep seeing Rockwell's mutated visage and "
"hearing Mei-Yin's words. Is this how he felt, towards the end?\n"
"\n"
"Well I won't make his mistakes. Mei-Yin, Raia, Santiago and all the others "
"who have helped me get here made sure of that. I'll only use the prism if I'm "
"sure it can't hurt the people I care about, and if that means never learning "
"the ultimate truth of the ARKs? So be it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2039672569"
msgid ""
"After taking the Painted Sharks' last foothold on the mainland, this war has "
"turned into one of attrition. While I construct a proper fleet, the Sharks' "
"resources will continue to dwindle and my flyers will continue to harass "
"their main compound. When we finally stage our invasion, their spirits will "
"be broken and their storehouses empty.\n"
"\n"
"In the meantime, I've been investigating this island's potential for naval "
"warfare. Some sea creatures can carry a small ballista  platform on their "
"back, making them a curious sort of warship. I'm interested to see how "
"they'll fare. Hopefully the Sharks can offer a skirmish or two before their "
"will breaks completely.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3139562477"
msgid ""
"After that weirdness with Uma last night, it's obvious I've never really "
"gotten to know her at all.\n"
"\n"
"All the conscious stuff we humans do in our waking lives must be autonomic "
"for transhumans: listening to each other, shooting the shit, making "
"plans...\n"
"\n"
"I doubt they have to think about any of that unless they want to, any more "
"than we need to concentrate on breathing.\n"
"\n"
"I'll probably never get how she-or any of them-really thinks or feels.\n"
"\n"
"But I feel like I've been wasting my time even trying.\n"
"\n"
"It was their idea to bring me back and stuck me here!\n"
"\n"
"Have they only ever noticed me when I've managed to annoy them?\n"
"\n"
"Maybe I'd finally have their full attention if I went to central processing "
"right now and deleted their precious archive.\n"
"\n"
"It'd serve them right if I just walked in there and set off an EMP right in "
"the middle of the whole damned thing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1272697576"
msgid ""
