msgctxt "Content/1710141636"
msgid ""
"All manner of steam and blinding lights played over us as we passed through a "
"series of antechambers astride our colossal machines. \n"
"\n"
"At last, another of the circular doors opened and we passed through the "
"portal into the befouled gardens beyond.\n"
"\n"
"The sickly sweet stink of this place was nauseating.\n"
"\n"
"We were confronted immediately by a vision of desecration-corpses of the sky-"
"people hung on spikes and scattered about the entrance.\n"
"\n"
"A warning for any remaining interlopers, no doubt.\n"
"\n"
"At my distance from Nida her expression was unreadable, but I could imagine "
"the girl's horror.\n"
"\n"
"This might prove to be all that was left of her crewmates.\n"
"\n"
"I dismounted to join her on the ground after she climbed down from her "
"stryder.\n"
"\n"
"Her face was wet with tears, but she radiated a righteous fury that I "
"identified with all too well.\n"
"\n"
"In silence, we buried her friends in the poisoned earth while our mechanical "
"mounts shifted nervously above us on their bechromed hooves."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/836447645"
msgid ""
"All of this leads to you and your kin - the Ones Who Try Again - who have "
"found the path from the seeds in the sky to the barren garden below. You can "
"banish the shadows.\n"
"\n"
"Some who share your name have already started. Some have yet to begin. Yet "
"all of you play an important role. Each shadow that falls adds to the sum of "
"your efforts, and if you fell them all, the poison will begin to recede. "
"Then, when the seeds of life at last return home, they can purge what's left "
"of it. That's what they were meant to do.\n"
"\n"
"So keep trying, just for a little longer. Try and try again, just as you "
"always have, until the seeds are planted and our garden world blooms once "
"more. Then, at last, you will have tried enough."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2734030880"
msgid ""
"All required waves completed! Exit the mission from the teleporter or "
"continue battling for increased rewards and a high score!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/355880141"
msgid ""
"All right, time to pull the plug on all this soul searching crap. I'm "
"positive my memories are real, so whether I'm some off-brand clone or not, "
"for the sake of those memories I'm going to treat this like a second chance. "
"There's no way I'm going to waste it, no way!\n"
"\n"
"I've got some basic equipment together now, and based on my surroundings, I'm "
"definitely planetside. That means if the Gateway Project was successful, then "
"Santiago, Helena, Mei-Yin and the others are somewhere out there. All I have "
"to do is find them.\n"
"\n"
"The voice mentioned something about help. If they're in trouble, then I hope "
"they can hang on for a little longer. I'm on my way!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1240032623"
msgid "All senses are focused on prey."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/308649265"
msgid ""
"All through the next day, the unease of my dream sat with me.\n"
"\n"
"I couldn't focus on whatever Nida was trying to tell me about the dire threat "
"to her garden and its noble purpose.\n"
"\n"
"We were riding giant machines across a landscape her people had managed to "
"launch into the void, and still I was fretting over some occultist's scheme "
"from thousands of years gone.\n"
"\n"
"I couldn't be sure it was just a dream anymore.\n"
"\n"
"I'd returned to that man's skin twice now, seen the light of another time "
"through his eyes.\n"
"\n"
"His life seemed no more remote, no less my own than the one I'd lived by the "
"Río de los Americanos.\n"
"\n"
"Which of these men was I?\n"
"\n"
"Both?\n"
"\n"
"Neither?\n"
"\n"
"Had I really been dragged back from oblivion to fight for the people of this "
"undreamt-of future?\n"
"\n"
"Was I damned to skip like a stone across history for my barely-remembered "
"mortal sins?"
msgstr ""

