msgctxt "Content/3904591908"
msgid ""
"It ain't right! I killed the varmint that pretty-boy Trent was stuffing his "
"face with, and he's still got the stones to laugh at me just because I "
"stumbled over my words again. So what if I can't talk like Imamu? What's "
"Trent done, earn some trophies playing pigskin back home? I've been keeping "
"us alive!\n"
"\n"
"Still shouldn't have made a fuss over it. Boris had to hold me back or else "
"I'd have...and now? Trent's avoiding me, Imamu's scolding me and Emilia's too "
"scared to even look at me.\n"
"\n"
"It's like my second cousin, twice removed, Ernest, always said: if you lose "
"your temper, you'd best make sure you find it, because tempers are mighty "
"expensive."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/241719738"
msgid "It can live in peace now."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3609425769"
msgid ""
"It did not take long to find the entrance to the cave, and when we reached "
"it, Helena stirred. Though she did not awake completely, I could hear her "
"speaking to me.\n"
"\n"
"\"The Tomb of Ascension. Find the altar.\"\n"
"\n"
"There is no time to waste. I have left most of my beasts to guard the "
"entrance while I bring a trusted few  to clear the cave. There are pockets of "
"malformed creatures here, and before I can see to Helena, I will need to rid "
"the tomb of these these unnatural beasts and their poisoned blood.\n"
"\n"
"This close to my goal, there is an extra drop of fury flowing through my "
"veins, and any enemies that block my path today will be quickly torn asunder."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1736059357"
msgid ""
"It has been several days since I left Prophet's Rest, and I have seen no sign "
"of pursuit. I am unsurprised. They probably assumed that I would make for the "
"blue obelisk, as it was nearest. By setting out for the green obelisk "
"instead, I already outwitted those simple minded zealots. As I said – miles "
"ahead! Miles!\n"
"\n"
"With those fools out of the way, I can slow my pace and take some time to "
"properly study these so called sacred relics of theirs. I am curious to see "
"if the materials they are made of bear any similarity to the metal in the "
"starlit sanctuary."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2238591450"
msgid ""
"It has been such a blessing to be able to spread Hathor's joy and love to so "
"many people. At first, my daily prayers garnered but a few curious observers. "
"Yet soon, observations turned to questions, and questions turned to "
"participation. Now there are so many of us that we have even begun to "
"construct a shrine. \n"
"\n"
"I truly wish that I could teach these eager new students all day long, but my "
"duty to the village must come first. Perhaps when our future here is finally "
"secured I shall be able to live the life of a priestess again, but for now I "
"have too many people counting on me. I cannot abandon them."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1119030230"
msgid "It is here that she and her allies faced their final battles."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1134046362"
msgid ""
"It is no use. These machines are beyond my comprehension I cannot even make "
"the simplest of their tools work properly. Compared to this, training with a "
"spear or sword seems simple.\n"
"I have tried to earn my keep by helping with chores and other tasks, but I "
"usually get in the way or slow things down. Compared to the others, I am like "
"a child, and they treat me as such.\n"
"This was a mistake. I belong in the forest with the beasts, not among these "
"people in their glowing metal halls. I will ask them for supplies and depart "
"within the week."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1887382066"
msgid ""
"It is the chaos of this land that is truly disturbing to me, even more than "
"its most titanic and vicious beasts. Animals are meant to be savage. Even "
"when tamed, they are not truly civilized, but man? Man is supposed to be "
"above the animal, yet the people here live in squalor and fight viciously "
"over scraps like stray dogs.\n"
"\n"
"I have convinced some of them to band together under my leadership, and "
"together, we have found safety and order. Unfortunately, they are untrained "
"and lack cohesion. I'll have to fix that.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2391798465"
msgid "It needed to be done, Survivor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3167795033"
msgid ""
"It seems I was not the only one who was skeptical of Rockwell's ability to "
"curb my ambitions. The nearby Painted Sharks mustered up the courage to "
"harass several of our coastal fortresses, but in doing so, they confirmed "
"their nature. During their raids, they only attacked from the air and sea. "
"They patently refused to set foot on land.\n"
"\n"
"If the Sharks are at home in the ocean, then I will pull our coastal forces "
"back and attack their outposts on the mainland. Once their island fortress is "
"cut off from support and supplies, I can whittle it down to rubble at my "
"leisure.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4288906513"
msgid ""
"It seems that Prophet's Rest is less a fortress and more an enclave or "
"monastery. I suppose that would explain the name, now wouldn't it?\n"
"\n"
"Yes as strange as it may sound, the natives have created a primitive religion "
"centered around the ARK's obelisks. They pray three times a day, each time "
"facing a different obelisk, and their robes bear a unique symbol - a three "
"pointed star coloured red, green and blue. The blue obelisk appears to "
"receive particular reverence due to is proximity. \n"
"\n"
"As charmingly ignorant as their superstitions may be, it's far from the most "
"savage religion I've encountered. Besides, Prophet's Rest is in need of a "
"doctor, and I am in need of supplies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3029426414"
msgid ""
"It seems that some of our neighbors have grown weary of our raiding. Today, I "
"received an envoy from the Golden Arrows who proposed a lucrative trade "
"agreement between our two tribes, with the caveat that we never encroach on "
"the territory or convoys of the Golden Arrows or any of their allies.\n"
"\n"
"I have no interest in trade agreements, but I do know how to seize an "
"opportunity. So instead of accepting right away, I proposed that we ratify "
"the agreement with his tribe's leaders on a neutral site.\n"
"\n"
"I have planned long enough. It is time for the New Legion to resume its "
"march.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/232045756"
msgid ""
"It should just work! The MEKs' power systems fuse perfectly during my "
"teleportation sims, so why does the reactor keep sputtering? The errors I'm "
"getting don't make any sense, but if I ignore them and they turn out to be "
"right, the fusion process could end in a catastrophic reactor "
"meltdown.\n"
"\n"
"Unbelievable! Here of all places is where I screw up? The most critical "
"juncture of this entire damned enterprise?\n"
"\n"
"I'd never make a mistake like this back home, but maybe that's because the "
"original Santiago was better than I am. If I'm just a crude approximation "
"then some degradation would...no, I'm fixing this. Just like I always have."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3750344970"
msgid ""
"It took a beating, but with a little more work, I think I can get this beauty "
"running again.\n"
"\n"
"It won't take long to get used to the controls, either. They were clearly "
"designed so that even someone without a single hour in a simulator could take "
"the wheel on a more basic level, but there's a lot of advanced settings here "
"too. I'll have it dancing like a fifty ton ballerina in no time. It's enough "
"to make a girl giddy.\n"
"\n"
"Santiago, if you were here right now, I'd kiss you. You certainly deserve "
"more than the grave I made for you, so I'll just have to pay my respects by "
"showing off what your last brainchild can really do. Hope you're watching."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2623378020"
msgid ""
"It took time, but I finally pilfered enough supplies and tools to survive on "
"my own. Loading them onto these camel-like beasts of burden was laborious, "
"but the real trial was absconding with the artifacts.\n"
"\n"
"There is always someone watching the inner sanctum, so I carefully studied "
"the guard's shifts until I identified whose drink I had to spoil with my "
"knockout serum. Even then I acted with great haste and guile, for my heist "
"will surely be discovered when the priests convene for their morning "
"prayers.\n"
"\n"
"Alas, they will be too late! Sir Edmund Rockwell is always ahead of his foes, "
"but not by a mere step. No, I am miles and miles beyond their reach!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1009677244"
msgid ""
"It took weeks of searching, but I finally caught a glimpse of Wali al Aswad. "
"I knew I was getting close when I found a series of fulgurite formations this "
"morning, and sure enough, I spotted several wyverns later in the afternoon "
"with a lone rider among them. \n"
"\n"
"The rider clearly saw me too, because soon enough the wyverns were circling "
"overhead. I waved and yelled in greeting, even calling out Mei Yin's name "
"just in case. Yet without so much as a nod, the wyverns regrouped and flew "
"off.\n"
"\n"
"Wali's not a social butterfly it seems, but I'm not letting them off the hook "
"that easily."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1339783033"
msgid ""
"It turns out that I didn't find Wali al Aswad. She found me.\n"
"\n"
"While the portal I used to get here opened with little fanfare on my end, "
"apparently the other side created quite the spectacle. According to Wali, it "
"was easy for her to spot from atop her wyvern, and she started tailing me "
"soon afterwards. I guess her timely interventions were no coincidence. "
"\n"
"\n"
"She didn't seem very surprised when I told her about the obelisks, their "
"guardians or even that this desert is actually a space station. Either she "
"knows more than she's saying, or experience has grinded the surprise right "
"out of her."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1215222799"
msgid ""
"It was here that her fellow explorer Rockwell began his spiral into darkness."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/480560438"
msgid ""
"It was never normal. Always extraordinary. Always an enigma.\n"
"\n"
"The uses for it were beyond counting. Hardier than tungsten. More versatile "
"than copper. In the right form, its ability to generate electricity and "
"produce radiation were unrivaled. It's no surprise then that things moved "
"quickly - impact, discovery, invention and production. All in rapid "
"succession.\n"
"\n"
"It took generations to notice the change - far after the great cataclysm and "
"the rise of my elders. By then its roots had reached the far corners of the "
"garden, and still it spread. Replicating. Infecting. Those it had use for "
"became its shadows. The rest, it devoured."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1739012620"
msgid "It was this big!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4158410911"
msgid ""
"It wasn't too late to let go of the malice in my heart.\n"
"\n"
"That was what the angel assured me in the dreamworld that Nida dropped me "
"into, the one with the setting sun.\n"
"\n"
"Speaking of Nida, the girl pouted for hours after I reacted poorly to the "
"hallucination she forced on me.\n"
"\n"
"I couldn't understand why she seemed to expect praise for what she'd "
"done.\n"
"\n"
"I don't trust my own sensations, my own memories.\n"
"\n"
"I wonder if I've ever left perdition, if this ring of gardens might not be "
"another breaking wheel for my infernal soul.\n"
"\n"
"In the dark I lie awake, afraid to dream again, and wonder if this girl is "
"some demon assigned to torment me.\n"
"\n"
"And then his voice whispers to me, the one who woke me from Genesis and led "
"me to my armor.\n"
"\n"
"He tells me the angel lied."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2877420045"
msgid ""
"It worked. The prism, it worked, but I hesitated. Now we're only two. Only "
"two, everyone else is dead. Everyone else. Am I dying too? Is this how it "
"feels? Is that why I keep seeing the tomb? The tomb, again and again. The "
"tomb, the throne and the ladder.\n"
"\n"
"The ladder. I see it once more. I'm climbing still, above the clouds and into "
"the stars. I think I see the end, but when I try to grab the next rung, my "
"hand turns to dust. I try to scream, but I make no sound.\n"
"\n"
"I'm slipping away. I see their faces. Rockwell, Raia, Diana, Santiago, Mei-"
"Yin...I reach for them. I have to find purchase. There must be something I "
"can grasp. Something.\n"
"\n"
"The tomb. The tomb!"
msgstr ""

