msgctxt "Content/1028149714"
msgid ""
"Not everyone sees things the way I do, but that doesn't make them wrong. I "
"owe Mei-Yin for reminding me of that fact. I can't remember exactly what it "
"was I said to her, something about how the signal was the only thing in this "
"bloody wasteland that mattered, but her reply stopped me cold.\n"
"\n"
"\"Your voice just then, it sounded like Rockwell's.\"\n"
"\n"
"I didn't say much after that. For a change, Mei-Yin did most of the talking. "
"Unlike me, she doesn't care about the mysteries of this place. The space "
"stations, the end of the world, none of it. She just wants to keep us - me - "
"safe.\n"
"\n"
"I should be grateful for that. I mean, I am but...I need time to think."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1747845683"
msgid ""
"Not only is this berry-based coloring is great for decorating cakes, it also "
"doubles as a dye for clothing and buildings.\n"
"\n"
"18 Berries\n"
"Add 1-3 of a chemical catalyst\n"
"Submerge in Water\n"
"Cook in a Cooking Pot\n"
"\n"
"To make different colors:\n"
"1 - Use different berries in varying amounts\n"
"2 - Use a different catalyst, such as Charcoal or Gunpowder"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4039510278"
msgid ""
"Not so dumb now, am I, Boris? Hope you felt real smart while you were "
"bleeding out, bro!\n"
"\n"
"Imamu still thinks he could have talked psycho down, but I say screw him. The "
"dude attacked Imamu out of nowhere, then ran off to this weird ass room. He'd "
"completely lost it! \n"
"\n"
"Crazy or not though, he may have been onto something. Imamu says this place "
"Boris found might be related to that glowy thingy he was constantly staring "
"at. Something about a series of keys? I don't know, I let Imamu do the "
"thinking. I'm the big, handsome muscle of this operation, you know?\n"
"Hey, writing all this down actually feels pretty good. Think I'll do it more "
"often, at least when Imamu doesn't need to study Boris' notes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2675098936"
msgid ""
"Not too long ago, I thought this place was a far off utopia where I could "
"study all the world's lost wonders. Now that I'm fairly certain it's not "
"natural at all, I have to say, it's lost a lot of luster.\n"
"\n"
"Interference from mankind hasn't helped. Most tribes have learned to live in "
"harmony with their slice of the Island, but some aren't content with that. "
"One is even trying to conquer all the others, and natural or not, this "
"ecosystem won't be any better off if it's burned down in some great "
"war\n"
"\n"
"The sunrises are still beautiful, though. At least nothing can change that."
msgstr ""

