msgctxt "Content/2128348180"
msgid ""
"Once I made contact with the stray colonist I explained where and when we "
"are, and tried to describe the threat we're facing.\n"
"\n"
"I'm guessing that was probably a lot to absorb, depending on information "
"recall from the Genesis simulation.\n"
"I beamed over some schematics of the local subsurface crawlways and conduits, "
"hopefully with the access hatches clearly highlighted.\n"
"\n"
"Then I shut it all down and waited.\n"
"\n"
"I had a long wait.\n"
"\n"
"Almost half a cycle passed before something tripped the silent alarm I'd set "
"on the hatches in this sector.\n"
"My heart was in my throat-what was I going to do if one of those "
"monstrosities found its way down here to me, wave a soil probe at "
"it?\n"
"\n"
"Lucky for me, it was just my new friend, the colonist.\n"
"\n"
"I took it as a good sign that my colonist friend was conscientious enough to "
"seal the hatch again.\n"
"\n"
"Plus, I wasn't alone anymore."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2689691314"
msgid ""
"Once I upgraded my Charge Lantern prototype to be vastly more portable and "
"efficient, the village council could ignore my petitions no longer. I shall "
"be accompanying an expedition to the lower caverns posthaste!\n"
"\n"
"At last, I shall be able to observe Edmundium in its rawest, most natural "
"state! Marvelous! I can hardly contain my excitement, though I must make an "
"effort to.\n"
"The barbarian woman has been glowering at me for days. I suspect if she "
"could, she would watch my every move, and probably forbid Diana from speaking "
"to me. Fortunately, Miss Walker has been distracting her with trivialities, "
"but I must still be cautious. That savage will turn to violence on a whim, "
"and I must not provoke her."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4034804824"
msgid "Once they do, all that life will be unleashed."
msgstr ""

