msgctxt "Content/3616636375"
msgid ""
"Our base is looking pretty fancy these days. We even had enough spare Element "
"to whip up some genuine Hyper Chambers. I'm feeling more rested than ever, "
"yet somehow just as restless. There's no sky to lose myself in anymore, "
"that's the problem. It's left me too much time to think.\n"
"\n"
"Weirdly, I keep coming back to my necklace, the Star of David one my mother "
"gave me. Sometimes I catch myself reaching for it, forgetting it's not there. "
"Why is that? I've never been too religious.\n"
"\n"
"Better take one of those gliders for a spin to clear my head - they're the "
"only way to fly now that our jetpacks stopped working. Maybe I'll think of "
"some dirtier jokes while I'm at it. Halsted one upped me on the last patrol "
"and I can't let that stand."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1014238390"
msgid ""
"Our research and development machinists were already hard at work building "
"out tools and gear for our future generational crew, so I felt bad piling "
"on.\n"
"\n"
"I wouldn't have bothered them if I didn't think my design was worth adding to "
"the R&D workload.\n"
"\n"
"There's no way a human crew could find and remove every trace of raw Element "
"contamination from the biomes on our colony ship without automation on a "
"massive scale.\n"
"\n"
"What good is authority though, if you can't abuse it for a worthy "
"cause?\n"
"\n"
"Besides, I have to admit it feels good to design something that's not some "
"kind of military tek.\n"
"\n"
"I like the idea of these things scrubbing away every trace of the toxin I'd "
"once helped pollute battlefields with.\n"
"\n"
"I probably shouldn't have kept my idea off the books for now, but I feel like "
"Uma won't shut this down once she sees a real world prototype of my stryder "
"concept."
msgstr ""

