msgctxt "Content/1890278487"
msgid ""
"So I confronted Uma, and she confirmed that I'm a clone of the original "
"Santiago.\n"
"\n"
"And yeah, they gave me false memories to cover for the time it took to back "
"up my personality and grow a new body to put it in.\n"
"\n"
"Wish I could say she seemed remorseful while confirming my most paranoid "
"fears.\n"
"\n"
"Uma just stood back and waited while I flipped out.\n"
"\n"
"Once I'd worn myself out, she pointed out that we were trying to save the "
"world here.\n"
"\n"
"In Uma's mind, the ends justified whatever means were necessary.\n"
"\n"
"They'd already restored me from a backup by the time I joined Genesis on the "
"condition that they didn't put me in their archive.\n"
"\n"
"She said I'd been given a leadership role as important as any human ever "
"had.\n"
"\n"
"There were politicians and military commanders who dreamed their whole lives "
"of being able to make a difference or leave a legacy like I would.\n"
"\n"
"Was she expecting gratitude?\n"
"\n"
"Imagine that."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2889409976"
msgid ""
"So I did something else impulsive, maybe even treasonous.\n"
"\n"
"Hey, someone had to try something!\n"
"\n"
"While almost everyone else was preoccupied with retaking the ship, I tried to "
"reestablish contact with HLN-A, that invasive intelligence I'd found in the "
"Genesis simulation.\n"
"\n"
"This time I used a sort of process of elimination.\n"
"\n"
"Assuming it managed to create a digital blind spot to hide in, I figured I "
"could find it by establishing where it wasn’t.\n"
"\n"
"Like using infrared to search for a heat signature against a "
"snowfield.\n"
"\n"
"Once I'd colored in all the negative space, I jumped into that void in the "
"simulation and found myself immediately pleading with the AI to stop the "
"corruption of our ship systems.\n"
"\n"
"I should've sent someone braver in to negotiate..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1086497987"
msgid ""
"So far so good. The cat has helped keep the critters away, so I've conserved "
"ammunition, and we're all stocked up on supplies. For the immediate future, "
"I'd say we're safe and secure.\n"
"\n"
"Further than \"immediate\" though? I'm not so sure. Neither of us are "
"builders, and there are bigger, tougher animals than long-toothed cats out "
"there. Eventually we'll need to find some new friends. Nosti was the biggest "
"settlement in the desert, but it couldn't have been the only one. \n"
"\n"
"I'd heard rumors that a hunting party had seen some buildings to the west. "
"Sounds like as good a place to start as any."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1625781569"
msgid ""
"So far, so good! We're making tons of progress on these artifacts, and I've "
"been feeling extra pumped lately. I think all my hype is even rubbing off on "
"Imamu. The other day we spent like, an hour joking about who's gonna play us "
"when we sell our story to Hollywood. Haven't seen him that chill since before "
"we lost Rusty.\n"
"\n"
"Pretty soon, we're gonna head deeper than we've ever been to find the last of "
"the artifacts. It won't be a tropical vacation or anything, but our teamwork "
"is on point right now, so bring it on!\n"
"\n"
"The lasers help, too. Teamwork and freaking lasers, baby!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2708123539"
msgid ""
"So much for that. Less than a day after I set out, my mission hit a wall, or "
"more specifically, an invisible energy barrier that extends around this "
"entire area. Definitely in my bottom ten landings of all time, by the way. My "
"shoulder's still feeling it.\n"
"\n"
"Once I reported back, I took Santiago to inspect the barrier. He thinks it's "
"also the culprit that's responsible for jamming our long range signals. So "
"basically, as long as this barrier exists, we have no way to reach the "
"outside world. We're completely isolated.\n"
"\n"
"Unless, of course, we find a way to take it down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3149133010"
msgid ""
"So the three of us met this morning, and Uma admitted that they shouldn't "
"have recorded Yongki for the archive without his consent.\n"
"\n"
"Then she gave him the same pitch I'd gotten, about how vital he was to "
"humanity's survival and the ends justifying the means.\n"
"\n"
"Yongki called Uma inhuman.\n"
"\n"
"She asked how she could prove to him she cared, and the kid challenged her to "
"come out drinking with us.\n"
"\n"
"All night, Yongki kept clumsily trying to pry information out of Uma.\n"
"\n"
"That backfired on him when she finally got tired of his badgering, and let us "
"know how little time anyone on Earth actually has left.\n"
"\n"
"After we absorbed that news, Yongki said he’d rather spend his remaining "
"years with his family.\n"
"\n"
"She told him she'll accept his resignation only if he still feels the same "
"when he sobers up.\n"
"\n"
"He swore he was going to stumble back on site and resign at the crack of late "
"afternoon tomorrow, but I really hope he doesn't."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1165598331"
msgid ""
"So this city's the ultimate fate of civilization, huh? A bunch of crumbling, "
"overgrown buildings, crawling with all the insects we left behind? I guess "
"you can't say no one warned us.\n"
"\n"
"A lot of people fought real hard to keep something like this from happening, "
"myself included, and turns out the apocalypse showed up anyway. I always "
"thought we'd stave it off myself. I guess I just believed in us, you know? "
"Humanity, I mean.\n"
"\n"
"But even knowing it was going to end up like this, I don't think I'd do "
"anything different. Regrets aren't my style. Besides, there's a few of us "
"humans still kicking. Who knows, someday these buildings could be full again, "
"but until then I get a spacious corner apartment rent free. Not too shabby."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4153113595"
msgid ""
"So, in addition to all of the oddities I found with wild megalodons, here's "
"the real cherry on top – taming them is a piece of piss. A bit of training "
"and they're more obedient than the family dog.\n"
"\n"
"Now, I've heard of sharks getting very rudimentary training over a year or "
"so, but not to this extent. Certainly not so easily. Sharks aren't mammals or "
"even avians, they're fish. They rely more on instinct, or to put it simply, "
"they're not very smart. You shouldn't be able to ride one like a jet "
"ski.\n"
"\n"
"I'm trying to keep an open mind like Rockwell suggested, but this just feels "
"wrong."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1163719237"
msgid ""
"So, quick update: this isn't a simulation.\n"
"We're really on a ginormous spaceship."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/257702080"
msgid ""
"So, these are the conquerors that I heard about way back when. Not a great "
"first impression. Mei-Yin and I weren't quite mates, but watching her "
"creatures get slaughtered like that certainly wasn't pleasant. I'm not a fan "
"of the prisoner lifestyle, either.\n"
"\n"
"The leader introduced himself as Gaius Marcellus Nerva, and he's not a "
"complete bogan, I'll give him that. He let me keep my personal effects and "
"our conversations have been civil so far. I get the feeling that'll change if "
"I don't cooperate, though.\n"
"\n"
"Not that I have much choice. They already took the keys. The only way I'm "
"seeing this through is as a \"guest\" of the New Legion."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3558790535"
msgid ""
"So, you ask, who are you? Well you're you, but not just once. You're you over "
"and over again.\n"
"\n"
"I'll rephrase: if our identity is defined by our actions, then what is yours? "
"Are you One Who Engages in Fisticuffs with Helpless Trees? No, what defines "
"you is that you try again. Should you starve, you try again. Should you fall "
"from a cliff, you try again. Should you be digested by some magnificent "
"predator, you try again.\n"
"\n"
"And now Earth, humanity, life...you can give all of it the chance to try "
"again too, because you and all your siblings who fell from the sky are the "
"Ones Who Try Again."
msgstr ""

