msgctxt "Content/885961712"
msgid ""
"These displays are perfect for showing off your Shoulder-pets, tiny Tames, "
"and Companions--all while providing some health and experience over time. "
"Comes in Nest and Bed varieties"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2695441441"
msgid ""
"These flippers are firm, but flexible.  Wearing them increases swim speed, "
"but decreases walking speed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2059191056"
msgid ""
"These halls did hide one marvel, I shall grant them that. I found it during "
"my patrols, tucked away in a small chamber all its own, and while I do not "
"know its purpose, its beauty is without question.\n"
"\n"
"It is shaped like a jewel, with a surface of polished stone and shimmering "
"metal, glowing proudly with a magnificent golden light. Though it floats "
"above the ground, it is too sturdy to move, and though its light is warm, it "
"is cool to the touch.\n"
"\n"
"Helena will surely want to see this. However, until we fully understand it, I "
"will be sure to supervise her study sessions."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1850496442"
msgid ""
"These incredibly sharp metal spikes are dangerous to any that touch them.  "
"Larger creatures take more damage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2211708296"
msgid ""
"These incredibly sharp wooden stakes are dangerous to any that touch them.  "
"Larger creatures take more damage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1389900608"
msgid ""
"These incredibly strong, lightweight nodules are somehow naturally made in "
"corrupted creatures. Incredibly hazardous to human health if consumed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3460056129"
msgid ""
"These incredibly strong, lightweight plates are somehow naturally made in "
"certain creatures. Incredibly hazardous to human health if consumed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/880134485"
msgid ""
"These incredibly strong, lightweight plates can be shaped and then heat "
"treated into casings for anything."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2303450881"
msgid ""
"These machines Santiago's building are brilliant! Somehow he's simplified the "
"controls so that even a weirdo biologist like me can move these big blokes as "
"if they're our own body. Me, piloting robots...I've completely lost control "
"of my life, honestly.\n"
"\n"
"Even Mei-Yin was able to synchronize with one, and for a second I swear she "
"cracked the tiniest of smiles. I think that brought me more relief than the "
"mechs themselves. She's fought so hard to get here, and been through so much, "
"especially that nightmare with Rockwell and Diana. I hope that at the end of "
"all this, I can help her find some shred of real happiness. She deserves it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2407972836"
msgid ""
"These obelisks are fascinating. Apparently, Rockwell managed to coax a "
"response out of one of them with an offering of some kind. Could it be that "
"they are some grand monument to the gods? If I appease them with a sacrifice, "
"will they grant me their power?\n"
"\n"
"Yes, of course. Janus may have chosen me to rule this island by bringing me "
"here, but I must prove my worth to the other gods by completing this ritual. "
"Well, now that I have Rockwell's council at my beck and call, I shall pass "
"this trial with ease. Then the power of the gods will be mine to "
"command.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2389698966"
msgid ""
"These pearls are made almost entirely of Silicon.  Can be refined into "
"Silicon plates."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/15541569"
msgid ""
"These titans remind me of combat drones. This control center has tracked "
"their general migration patterns, and to my eye, they're almost like troop "
"movements. When they decide to swarm something, they come from all over, like "
"something's commanding them. Not to mention they spread Element everywhere "
"they go. So basically, before the Reseed Protocol can be triggered, the "
"titans need to be eliminated.\n"
"\n"
"Normally I'd be all gung ho about an impossible mission like that, but the "
"number of titans we'd have to take down is nuts. Mei and I might be a killer "
"power couple, if I do say so myself, but even we'd die of old age before we "
"ever made a dent in the their population.\n"
"\n"
"There must be something we can do though. I did find lots of references to a "
"place called \"Arat Prime,\" off on the other side of the planet. Looks "
"promising, but...well now isn't that interesting. Our favorite mystery being "
"seems to think so too. Is that where it's leading us?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3626743656"
msgid ""
"They dare to lecture me? Me? Imbeciles! They claim to be from the future, but "
"they fear progress! I performed a miracle of science and their reaction is to "
"scold me like a child.\n"
"Damn them, damn them all! They'll never let me have another subject at this "
"rate. How am I to continue my experiments without subjects? They may let "
"their petty morality hold them back, but I won't let it bind me. Not when I'm "
"this close.\n"
"I know with certainty now that Edmundium can unlock a species' potential, I "
"just have to perfect the process. Even without subjects, I must find a way. I "
"must!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4019654298"
msgid ""
"They were here, no doubt about that. There's scoring from TEK weapons all "
"over, and while I can't pin down exactly how old they are, the gaps they "
"burned in the foliage mean they're not ancient. The caliber on some of these "
"are huge though, way bigger than a rifle. Don't tell me Santiago built a "
"freaking tank?\n"
"\n"
"Guess I'll find out soon enough. The tugging on my mind is growing stronger. "
"Something's nearby that the voice wants me to see. Whatever it is, I'd better "
"take a careful approach. I'm not exactly brimming with firepower, and I don't "
"have Mei's gift for taming animals, so I'm all alone here. Can't afford any "
"dumb mistakes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1556694675"
msgid ""
"They weren't exaggerating when they said the surface was dangerous. Direct "
"exposure to sunlight during the day will quickly burn a human to a crisp, "
"even in this fancy armor.\n"
"That means we have to adjust our sleep schedules and wait just below the "
"surface until night falls. When it does, we'll make a mad dash for the "
"obelisk, let Santiago get in as much work as he dares, then run our asses "
"back to safety.\n"
"Strewth! I thought that bloody desert was diabolical, but this tops it for "
"sure! Why couldn't we do something simple, like flee from a pack of ravenous "
"Allosaurus or something? This life I lead, I swear..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2370818560"
msgid ""
"They're talking about detaching our ring if things keep getting worse, to try "
"to keep our biomes uncontaminated.\n"
"\n"
"I hope it doesn't come to that, but we have to do what we can to preserve the "
"remaining biomes in the face of our rapidly dwindling odds.\n"
"\n"
"I've been working on a whole system of backup automation to hopefully keep "
"everything running as long as possible when-I mean if-we're all wiped "
"out.\n"
"\n"
"Our ship holds the last archival specimens of life from Earth, and there's an "
"extinction-level event in progress.\n"
"\n"
"I got nauseous just now while I was running microbial gas exchange models, "
"because any stupid mistake I make could suffocate all the remaining Terran "
"lifeforms in the universe.\n"
"\n"
"If I forget to carry a number someplace, it could mean that no flower will "
"ever push up through the soil and bloom again.\n"
"\n"
"I have to get this right."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2882134676"
msgid ""
"They've sealed off the invaded areas of our ship, but I still have my "
"clearance to access the maintenance subsystems.\n"
"\n"
"I know how to get through a series of airlocks into the other ring without "
"contaminating ours.\n"
"\n"
"Once I popped up from under the dirt, I found myself in some kind of "
"unrecognizable surrealist landscape.\n"
"\n"
"What could have changed everything there so much, so fast?\n"
"\n"
"I was glad I'd brought a sampling kit and even more glad I was wearing a "
"clean suit up there.\n"
"\n"
"The flora and fauna had been mutated to a point where everything looked "
"potentially lethal, and it was reactive to my presence.\n"
"\n"
"Grasses had become these thin tubules with bulblike structures that undulated "
"hypnotically.\n"
"\n"
"I flinched when a stalk brushed my glove and left a sticky residue.\n"
"\n"
"Inside my clean suit I started shuddering all over, and wondering why I'd "
"worked so hard to sneak into that place."
msgstr ""

