msgctxt "Content/2903635381"
msgid ""
"Wali has been much quieter since we found Rockwell. I guess she's just "
"letting us catch up. However, she did say something interesting when we were "
"recounting Nerva's ambitions for the Island.\n"
"\n"
"\"This place would never allow anyone to master it,\" she said, and when I "
"asked her to explain, she told me that the great city to the southeast was "
"destroyed by the obelisk itself. \n"
"\n"
"Now it's just conjecture, but it's interesting to think about. Could the "
"curators of these stations be monitoring human behavior and clipping its "
"wings should the survivors ever band together and fly too close to the sun? "
"If each station represents a different group in a larger experiment, "
"\"resetting\" human progress would make a lot of sense. \n"
"\n"
"It's a bit grim though, isn't it? Yikes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/26189525"
msgid "Walk"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2805301722"
msgid "Walk Tamed Creatures onto this while active to grind them into Kibble."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4183047494"
msgid ""
"Walk Tamed Creatures onto this while active to grind them into Kibble. "
"Requires Power to activate."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1929643991"
msgid ""
"Walker had told us to expect some kind of monster after activating the "
"obelisk, but I never imagined that we would battle one of Ceres' dragons. No, "
"that's not right. It was too colossal and wild for even a god's chariot. I "
"doubt Diana herself could control it, and yet, the New Legion felled "
"it.\n"
"\n"
"It cost the lives of many men and even more beasts, but it was worth the "
"sacrifice. According to Walker, the third key we acquired may allow me to "
"open this cave she speaks of. Then the power of the obelisks and this very "
"island will be mine to command.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

