msgctxt "Content/4179278678"
msgid ""
"Welcome back to Earth.\n"
"\n"
"If you're reading this, maybe I didn't make it.\n"
"\n"
"Whatever -- as long as someone's there to read this note, that means there's "
"still at least one survivor left.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Our world's not what it used to be.\n"
"\n"
"Find yourself some shelter from the titans, and... just hang in there, "
"okay?\n"
"\n"
"Personal Note: yea, there are titans now..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1070268814"
msgid "Welcome to ARK! Equip a Tyrannosaurus with this to live the high life."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2559726853"
msgid ""
"Well protected against cold temperatures, & immune to contracting certain "
"Lesser Diseases!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1537741807"
msgid ""
"Well we ain't in Kentucky no more, I can tell you that. Never heard of a cave "
"this big, and sure as hell ain't heard of no glowing rocks. Even Uncle "
"Chester'd be pinching himself if he could see this, and he thinks a tribe of "
"mutant squirrels runs the government.\n"
"Good news: I ain't in this boat alone. Bad news: I'm sharing it with a bunch "
"of know-it-all city boys and one quiet city girl. Maybe they know what's what "
"in a classroom, but they're all wet behind the ears when it comes to real "
"survival. Man versus nature and all that.\n"
"\n"
"Looks like it'll be up to me to save the day then. Like my pappy always said: "
"if you want a cat skinned right, do it your damn self.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3195069902"
msgid ""
"Well, I found a new best mate. The little fuzzball isn't exactly what I "
"meant, but I'll take her.\n"
"\n"
"I've dubbed her species Renopila amplexus. They're small, cuddly little "
"herbivores, and as far as I can tell, taming one has no practical use. I just "
"couldn't let the her starve to death, though. I guess all this rubbish with "
"golems and wyverns has quelched what was left of my scientific instinct to "
"leave nature to nature.\n"
"\n"
"At least we provide each other with a little warmth at night, and her antics "
"have helped to keep my spirits up. I suppose I'll need to give her a name."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2897466482"
msgid ""
"Well, I found the reports on Mister Nerva to be rather exaggerated, and as an "
"Englishman, one might imagine that I'd view Roman leadership with some "
"disdain. Yet, in my experience, I found Mister Nerva to be both honest and "
"intellectually engaging.\n"
"In fact, after a lengthy conversation, I daresay that Mister Nerva has the "
"right of it when it comes to this island's politics. As the Romans created "
"Pax Romana, perhaps this New Legion will create Pax Arcam. Even if it "
"doesn't, I doubt it will harm my research, so I see no reason to interfere in "
"this particular squabble."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2241023675"
msgid ""
"Well, I found the reports on Mister Nerva to be rather exaggerated, and as an "
"Englishman, one might imagine that I'd view Roman leadership with some "
"disdain. Yet, in my experience, I found Mister Nerva to be civil, honest and "
"intellectually engaging.\n"
"In fact, after a lengthy conversation, I daresay that Mister Nerva has the "
"right of it when it comes to this island's politics. As the Romans created "
"Pax Romana, perhaps this New Legion will create Pax Arcam. Even if it "
"doesn't, I doubt it will harm my research, so I see no reason to interfere in "
"this particular squabble."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1472561793"
msgid ""
"Well, I think I've gotten as far in my studies of the obelisk as my "
"archeological expertise will take me. A shame, really. This has been such a "
"joyous little diversion that I hate to see it end.\n"
"\n"
"Ah, Rockwell you old twit! You've forgotten the origins of this little "
"excursion – spelunking! Did you yourself not hypothesize that there may be "
"more artifacts hidden elsewhere on this island? Surely you can't give up "
"before confirming that.\n"
"\n"
"No, certainly not, nor can I be expected to scour the ARK's caverns alone. "
"Perhaps someone can spelunk in my stead? Better yet, perhaps someone has "
"already spelunked!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3716601776"
msgid ""
"Well, I'm not dead, and as it turns out, neither was Mei-Yin. In fact, it was "
"her who freed me, and insisted we follow Nerva through the portal in the "
"cave. \n"
" \n"
"A horrifying scene awaited us. All of Nerva's men and a large, bizarre "
"creature lay dead in a heap, but Nerva's body was missing. Forgetting my "
"present company, I suggested a peaceful approach if we encountered him. That "
"earned me one hell of a knockout punch.\n"
" \n"
"When I came to, I searched the whole station, but the only signs of Mei-Yin "
"and Nerva were a few ounces of dried blood. No bodies, and no victor. \n"
" \n"
"Yet what I did find was fascinating. It was quickly evident that I was on "
"some kind of space station, but when I looked out one window in particular, I "
"realized something even more surprising – I'd been on a space station the "
"whole time.\n"
" \n"
"There, floating outside the window and surrounded by machinery, was the very "
"island that I had been living on, and it too was orbiting high above the "
"surface of some unknown planet. The ecosystem on the Island wasn't just "
"curated, it was completely artificial from the ground up!\n"
" \n"
"What in the hell is all this, and why would anyone construct it? I don't have "
"the slightest clue at the moment, but somehow, I mean to find out. Somehow, "
"I'll find the truth.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1907450752"
msgid ""
"Well, I've combed through more carnivore droppings than I care to calculate, "
"and I can't say they provided many answers. All the predators in this region "
"have very similar diets. With so many different predators hunting the same "
"prey, the populations of all these species shouldn't be sustainable. Yet I've "
"found nothing to indicate that any population shift is actually "
"happening.\n"
"\n"
"It's just bizarre! The longer I'm here, the more I realize that this region "
"shouldn't exist. Its climate is out of sync with the rest of the island, many "
"of the creatures here are millions of years ahead of the dinosaurs and the "
"ecosystem is almost static!\n"
"\n"
"Something's off. I need to review my notes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3075992001"
msgid ""
"Well, I've survived worse!\n"
"I promise you I will find a way out of this, I will!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1175583680"
msgid ""
"Well, Yongki made me regret pushing him to share what his deal was with "
"me.\n"
"\n"
"Dunno what I expected, but it sure wasn't some conspiracy theory about my "
"background...\n"
"\n"
"I could see the kid was still on edge even after the time off with his "
"family, so I dragged him back to the canteen for another one-on-one.\n"
"\n"
"It only took a couple rounds of shots for him to open up.\n"
"\n"
"First he told me he'd heard a rumor that I'd been killed near the end of the "
"war.\n"
"\n"
"Then he admitted to trying to access my personnel file for proof of life, "
"only to find himself locked out.\n"
"\n"
"Even though he'd admitted to crossing a serious line, I laughed it off and "
"pointed out I was sitting right there next to him.\n"
"\n"
"I stopped laughing when he told me he'd found a listing for my engram in his "
"archive that was non-accessible, even at his security level.\n"
"\n"
"That was news to me."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1748192278"
msgid ""
"Well, looks like I'm off on another impossible mission. It's been way too "
"long, if you ask me.\n"
"\n"
"So those abandoned structures that scout team spotted a while back? Well "
"we're still not sure who left them there, but Santiago says that he's "
"detecting the emissions from what could be hypercharged, crystallized Element "
"shards in their vicinity. We need those for the Gateway Project's focusing "
"lens, and we haven't been able to make them ourselves.\n"
"\n"
"The trouble is, we can't even survive down there without hazard suits, and "
"half of that scout team got torn to pieces by the nastiest, ugliest creatures "
"we've ever seen. This could get bumpy..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4052814076"
msgid ""
"Well, the Howling Wolves are quickly tracking down the artifacts, but after "
"hearing about what happened to the Iron Brotherhood, that's as far as they'll "
"go. It's understandable, but it leaves me in a tight spot. If a giant spider "
"and I get in a scrap, the spider's winning for sure.\n"
"\n"
"Even with Athena on my side, I prefer to avoid danger, not confront it. My "
"aim's piss poor and I've got fists like marshmallows. If I want a fair go at "
"actually surviving whatever happens when the obelisk activates, I'll need "
"backup.\n"
"\n"
"Negotiation Notes: Don't mention feces. Don't look directly at the glare. "
"Bring chili (UNBURNED)."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2401335901"
msgid ""
"Well, this seals it. Just when I thought I'd made some sense of the notes I "
"took while visiting the Painted Sharks, I spotted the nail in the proverbial "
"coffin – roos. A whole herd of giant roos were just hopping about the "
"countryside like they'd always been there.\n"
"\n"
"As much as I love roos, they just shouldn't be here, period. They evolved in "
"Oz and Oz only sixty million years after dinosaurs went extinct among a bevy "
"of other marsupials. If I know any genus, it's this one, and procoptodon "
"should not exist here.\n"
"\n"
"This island isn't an ecosystem, it's a zoo."
msgstr ""

