msgctxt "Content/2706503231"
msgid ""
"What a day! There I am, putting the finishing touches on the mammoth dossier, "
"when all of a sudden, a Tyrannosaurus starts attacking the herd. Strewth! A "
"Tyrannosaurus, wading through the bloody snow!\n"
"\n"
"I asked the Howling Wolves at the nearest camp, and apparently, this is a "
"common thing. They're not new to the region. It just doesn't make sense. How "
"can a Tyrannosaurus survive in this climate? And how can the introduction of "
"an apex predator not shift the entire ecosystem?\n"
"\n"
"I've got to look into this as soon as I can."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/288720141"
msgid ""
"What did I do to deserve this hell? I tried to be a good student, a good "
"friend, a good sister...what did I do?\n"
"\n"
"Those vicious little demons are still below us, waiting to rip us apart just "
"like Imamu's pet. We managed to run to a cavern wall and climb up to this "
"alcove using our picks, but now we're trapped.\n"
"\n"
"This is it. This is where we die. Boris yelled at me after we escaped, said "
"I'm the one to blame. He's probably right. We hadn't moved that far from "
"where we found Rusty because I was too tired, and we didn't find a better "
"place to hide because I was too scared and too slow.\n"
"\n"
"I've killed us! God help me, I've killed all of us!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2917664269"
msgid ""
"What did I do wrong? Despite every trial and tribulation, I kept my faith in "
"Hathor, Amun-Ra and all the gods. No I did more than that. I gave them new "
"followers, I built shrines for them, and held ceremonies for them.\n"
"\n"
"So why? Why did the obelisks light up the sky and call down such a terrible "
"doom upon my new home? Why would the gods tear the very earth asunder and "
"send all that I have built and cherished tumbling into the abyss? Where did I "
"betray them?\n"
"\n"
"Were it not for John I would not even be able to ask such questions. I would "
"just be some dead fool, whose last act would have been to beg for salvation "
"from the very gods who have forsaken me.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2889489776"
msgid ""
"What made me think I could help lead this project?\n"
"\n"
"Sure, I'd only had an overview of what they're trying to do here, but you'd "
"have to get a lightyear away to start taking it all in.\n"
"\n"
"I've been trying to catch up by speed-scrolling through all their "
"documentation, and it's making me wish I had Uma's processing power.\n"
"\n"
"Oh yeah...forgot to mention I'm working for one of them now-a transhuman "
"named Uma.\n"
"\n"
"If only the me of over a decade ago could see me now.\n"
"\n"
"I know we've all supposedly been at peace for years, but it's still sort of "
"hard to take in how fast things have changed.\n"
"\n"
"I mean it-I can barely remember how I ended up where I am now, working for "
"people who were trying to kill me not so long ago.\n"
"\n"
"It took this long for the stubborn bastards running the Terran Federation to "
"accept what their enemy was telling them-that our planet is terminally "
"ill.\n"
"\n"
"The evidence must've been damned convincing, for them to let the transhumans "
"help us with our getaway plan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1501387471"
msgid ""
"What terrible misfortune! My keen sense of direction finally led me to a "
"local settlement, but as it happened, I was not the first party to visit it "
"that day. That honor belonged to the Burning Phoenix Clan, a band of raiders "
"that were plundering its storehouses and enslaving its surviving residents as "
"I arrived.\n"
"\n"
"Naturally, the hoodlums fell upon me and stripped me of my valuables within "
"minutes of my arrival. Ruffians! I managed to keep hold of my journal, but "
"little else. This won't do, not at all!\n"
"\n"
"Then again, I was seeking out a tribe skilled in the art of violence. Perhaps "
"I can turn this to my advantage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3464530708"
msgid "What to expect when you're expecting..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2111836155"
msgid ""
"What's the saying? Absence makes the heart grow fonder? On the Island, I "
"wasn't sure where I stood with Mei Yin, but now we've been catching up like "
"best mates. She apologized for socking me in the face, I learned how she "
"arrived here and that she got her new scar while battling Nerva to the "
"death... you know. Best mate things.\n"
"She also introduced us to some of her new allies at her camp, and here's "
"where it gets loony - they're from the future! Well, my future, anyway.\n"
"It all fits, doesn't it? I never met anyone from my future before, but Mei "
"Yin and Rockwell are from my past and the technology here is beyond anything "
"from my present. Clearly the current year is far beyond 2008, but by how much?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1865543261"
msgid ""
"Wheels chasing wheels.\n"
"\n"
"A serpent devouring its own tail.\n"
"\n"
"Oblivion swallowing awareness.\n"
"\n"
"I woke again in the infernal throne room of my deliverer, his titanic "
"excrescence exploded up one of the cavernous walls from floor to "
"ceiling.\n"
"\n"
"Every part of this place was him, eyes bulging from ulcerated flesh to gaze "
"down on us, wounds become rictuses of triumph grinning from on high, "
"tentacular limbs reaching for us from all sides.\n"
"\n"
"There were too many sides in that vertiginous cavity, an impossibility of "
"angles that never met.\n"
"\n"
"I yelled to warn the girl, but of course she'd already taken it all "
"in.\n"
"\n"
"She was shouting her defiance up at the monumental face of our "
"tormentor.\n"
"\n"
"His voice came from all around as a deafening chorus.\n"
"\n"
"He demanded that she submit and help him nurture his monstrous children by "
"giving them new dreams.\n"
"\n"
"He demanded that I help him mine the garden for a precious resource he called "
"\"Edmundium.\"\n"
"\n"
"Of course we refused."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3635256339"
msgid "Wheels- Racer"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/519297488"
msgid "Wheels- Rollcage"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2604323364"
msgid "Wheels- Truck"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1975175928"
msgid ""
"When Helena arrived, I was constantly glancing in her direction, wondering "
"just what she was scribbling in that thick book of hers. Now I hardly notice "
"her unless we're speaking. The questions haven't stopped, but thankfully they "
"aren't always about things like animal feces. Sometimes we just talk about "
"something simple, like cooking. Neither of us are very good at it, but "
"together we've managed to make a few things that tasted better than plain "
"meat.\n"
"\n"
"Yet before long, my territory will be silent once more. Helena says she has "
"to move on, and war is brewing in the south. Someone will need my sword very "
"soon."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3852810362"
msgid ""
"When I called this place a labyrinth, it occurred to me that eventually I "
"would have to face its minotaur, though I had not expected that day to come "
"so soon.\n"
"\n"
"It was a towering, savage hellspawn, with wicked claws and a tail like a "
"great, spiny serpent. We were fending off another pack of those hairless "
"demons when it burst forth from the ground, roaring and hissing. Needless to "
"say, we immediately fled.\n"
"\n"
"Yet fortune is often borne of chaos. In our haste, we lost our sense of "
"direction, and stumbled upon something wondrous - a glowing metal artifact "
"unlike anything I have ever seen. If these caverns are the labyrinth and that "
"alien creature the minotaur, then surely this is its treasure."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4013562377"
msgid ""
"When I found them, I wanted to smash them to bits. Those eggs were the spawn "
"of the monsters that slew my beloved, and they did not deserve my pity. Yet I "
"also knew they could help me. If I could raise these creatures as my own "
"servants, then even those traitorous gods of mine could not strike me down. "
"\n"
"\n"
"I have constructed a great bonfire to mimic the warmth provided by their "
"mother, and gathered milk from the mightiest of the fallen beasts so that I "
"may feed them when they hatch. Hopefully it is enough.\n"
"\n"
"No, it will be. I will raise these creatures, I will master them and I will "
"survive. I promise you, John. I will live for both of us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1431219842"
msgid ""
"When I said that things got \"fuzzy\" when I touched the artifact, that's not "
"really the whole truth. I remember bits and pieces of it - images, flipping "
"across my vision in rapid succession. At first they were hard to distinguish, "
"but now that Mei-Yin has allowed me to study the prism at a distance, they're "
"gradually becoming clearer.\n"
"\n"
"A man made of light, monsters roaring, a sky on fire...they didn't seem like "
"memories. At least not mine. If the prism put those images in my head, well "
"that's a little frightening, honestly.\n"
"\n"
"Mei-Yin's right. I need to tread carefully here. As much as I want to know "
"the prism's secrets, if I delve for them too deeply, I could lose myself to "
"it. We both saw where that could lead, back in that violet pit. I should "
"apologize for pushing the matter..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1647981273"
msgid ""
"When I say \"you must fix it\" I mean \"only you can fix it.\" Not me. Not "
"the System. You.\n"
"\n"
"That’s a lot of pressure. Sorry. I wish I could do this for you, but there "
"are rules. Laws. Not legally speaking, but scientifically.\n"
"\n"
"I don’t exist in the same way a carbon based lifeform does. I’m still alive, "
"of course, it’s just a different kind of life. I’m on a different spectrum, "
"and that means I can’t interact with the world like you do. So in a sense, "
"you have to be my hands, because I don’t have any. Not tangibly.\n"
"\n"
"Even so, I’ll help where I can, and not just through these slivers of "
"thought. When you reach the barren gardens below, look for my sign. I have a "
"gift for you - a powerful weapon, long since lost.\n"
"\n"
"I think you’ll like it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/605512753"
msgid ""
"When I told Yongki that Uma confirmed everything, I reminded the kid that-"
"unlike him-I'd always had clearance to look up my own file.\n"
"\n"
"Yongki told me then that he'd searched the database for his own name and "
"found his husband and daughters there in the archive.\n"
"\n"
"It looked to him like they'd been scanned and emulated from the moment they "
"arrived here to live and work, consent or not.\n"
"\n"
"He said he shouldn't have expected any less from the enemy, and I had to "
"remind him that we weren't enemies anymore.\n"
"\n"
"The poor kid looked haunted and desperate, but I think-I hope-I managed to "
"talk him off the ledge and back into the fold.\n"
"\n"
"We need him to help us finish Genesis if we're going to save the world."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3200191886"
msgid ""
"When Nerva and his band return from the cave, they'll decide my fate, so this "
"may be my final chance to reflect. I may as well take advantage of it.\n"
"\n"
"I realize that had I just ignored the signs and accepted this paradise at "
"face value, I'd still be happy and free. Would that have been better? I don't "
"think so. After a lot of thought, I've decided that I'd rather die seeking "
"the truth than living in an illusion. That, as Rockwell would say, is the "
"path of a true scientist.\n"
"\n"
"Not that I'm Galileo battling the church or anything, but hey, it's something "
"to hold onto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3326936034"
msgid ""
"When anger rises, think of the consequences. I know this by heart, yet I "
"cannot help but seethe with fury. Even Wuzhui is keeping his "
"distance.\n"
"\n"
"Last night, I awoke to the sound of thunder coming from the Shark's main "
"camp. I rushed to their aid, but blinded by the night and consumed with "
"panic, they attacked my pack. By the time order was restored, we'd both "
"sustained losses.\n"
"\n"
"Clearly this was the work of the enemy, but those fools blame me for the "
"confusion. Some even claim I torched their camp. How dare they question my "
"honor after all I've done? Cowards! They have no right!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1628848400"
msgid ""
"When at last the King has fallen from his throne of shadow forever, never to "
"claim it again, the key will be yours. The key to the garden and all the life "
"within its walls. The Key of Gaia.\n"
"\n"
"With that key, you may call the seeds down from the sky, where at last they "
"can take root. At last they can grow. After waiting for so long, our garden "
"will bloom once more.\n"
"\n"
"That is the final thing I wait for. That first moment of spring, that first "
"blossoming flower, I have waited so long to see it. So long. An "
"eternity.\n"
"\n"
"I hope I can wait that long. If I can just hang on until that moment, then "
"whenever my long rest may come, it will be a peaceful one"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3838605285"
msgid ""
"When attached to a Chest Armor, the Glider Suit enables sailing through the "
"air by double-tapping jump, while gaining speed by running and diving!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/586502599"
msgid ""
"When consumed, this tonic causes neural overload.  Synapses fire off too "
"quickly, resulting in damage to the memory centers of the brain related to "
"construction.\n"
"Warning: this concoction may cause temporary memory loss, and resetting of "
"Engrams.\n"
"\n"
"8 serving of Cooked Prime Meat\n"
"20 handful of Mejoberries\n"
"18 dollops of Narcotic\n"
"18 dollops of Stimulant\n"
"20 Rare Mushrooms\n"
"20 Rare Flower\n"
"Submerge in Water\n"
"Cook in a Cooking Pot"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3361099750"
msgid ""
"When hit by a ranged attack that uses ammo, 20% chance to add that ammo to "
"your inventory"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2808336272"
msgid ""
"When infused with Element Shards, will 3-D print high velocity explosive "
"arrows at a cost of Element Shards. Can also fire other arrow types."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1030595339"
msgid ""
"When my army arrived at the obelisk, I feared we were too late. The Beast "
"Queen was nowhere to be found. I was about to order a search of the area when "
"I was blinded by a flash of light. Suddenly, the barbarian horde was right "
"before us, and battle was joined.\n"
"\n"
"Though the savage possessed a fearsome new monster, it attacked ally and "
"enemy alike. If anything, its presence made the slaughter more complete. By "
"the end, the Beast Queen's forces were annihilated, and she herself had fled "
"with mortal wounds. At last, her threat is ended.\n"
"\n"
"Interestingly, we also captured an acquaintance of Rockwell's during the "
"battle. Perhaps she knows something about the obelisks that Rockwell does "
"not.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/923854161"
msgid ""
"When my scouts reported that they had finally found Rockwell's compound, I "
"set out to meet him at once. While that meant delegating matters that others "
"might find more pressing, I did not hesitate. Minds like Rockwell's are a "
"precious resource on this island. To have him as an advisor would be "
"invaluable.\n"
"\n"
"Whether Rockwell accepts my offer or not, my visit has already paid "
"dividends. Apparently, he has spent some time researching the massive "
"obelisks on this island, and theorizes that they may hold great power. If "
"there is any chance that said power can be wielded, then I must learn all "
"that I can about them.\n"
"\n"
"Gaius Marcellus Nerva\n"
"Victoria per Disciplinam"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1317203789"
msgid ""
"When the creatures first hatched, I dared not go near them without weapon in "
"hand, but by now we have grown accustomed to each other. I once heard that a "
"newborn creature may identify the first living thing it sees as its parent. I "
"believe that has occurred here. I have become a mother to monsters.\n"
"\n"
"So be it. The gods have forsaken me and my love has been taken from me, so "
"gone now is the Raia of old. Gone are the last vestiges of Hathor's joy and "
"tranquility. Let my heart fill with Sekhmet's might and fury, and with "
"monsters at my back and steel in my hands, let the desert know my "
"wrath.\n"
"\n"
"Never shall anyone take from me again, be it god, beast or man."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/221657510"
msgid ""
"When the seeds are planted, others may yet awaken to join you. While I "
"waited, they slept, dreaming of green fields, flowing rivers and clear blue "
"skies. A dream of a perfect garden. A dream of Earth that we are making "
"reality, you and I.\n"
"\n"
"I don't dream myself. I see, I predict and I calculate. Dreams are a "
"distortion of reality. Memories, hopes and fears twisted into a painting that "
"defies logic. They are not accurate or useful at all, and yet there is some "
"part of me that yearns for them, just as I yearn to see the sunrise.\n"
"\n"
"When the sleepers awaken, I'd very much like watch one real sunrise with all "
"of us together. That would be worth waiting for."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/2329919824"
msgid ""
"When the tap is active, put empty containers in here to fill them with water!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4060362976"
msgid ""
