msgctxt "Content/1201655814"
msgid ""
"With Camp Omega compromised, we've decided to head for the wastes. There's "
"not many of us left, and there's only three mechs remaining - piloted by Mei-"
"Yin, myself and a fiery URE bloke named Kazuma - so we can't form that super "
"weapon Santiago designed. That means if we run into anything too big or too "
"nasty, it'll be trouble.\n"
"\n"
"Yet we don't have a choice. The answers are somewhere in that wasteland, and "
"hopefully safety along with them.\n"
"\n"
"God, this whole piloting thing still feels bizarre, but I guess my nervous "
"system just linked up with the machine really well. And it's what I wanted, "
"isn't it? I'm finally something more than dead weight for other people to lug "
"around, I can do my part. I just hope I don't let everyone down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/469456244"
msgid ""
"With a mastery of one's equilibrium, no simple poison nor toxin can be a "
"threat.\n"
"<RichColor Color=\"1,0,0,1\">Only one of these may be carried at a time by an "
"organism.</>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1120147238"
msgid ""
"With craft and cunning, to look out for one's self may be essential to "
"survival.\n"
"<RichColor Color=\"1,0,0,1\">Only one of these may be carried at a time by an "
"organism.</>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3196705198"
msgid ""
"With craft and strategy, to outwit one's opponents may be essential to "
"survival.\n"
"<RichColor Color=\"1,0,0,1\">Only one of these may be carried at a time by an "
"organism.</>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3208665377"
msgid ""
"With relentless determination, the hunter will never waiver until it catches "
"its prey.\n"
"<RichColor Color=\"1,0,0,1\">Only one of these may be carried at a time by an "
"organism.</>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3000954191"
msgid ""
"With the MEKs entering their final phase of construction, I decided to give "
"our pilot team a little reward and simulate the MegaMEK fusion procedure. We "
"won't be able to do it for real for another couple weeks, but the sim is "
"pretty accurate.\n"
"\n"
"It went a lot better than I expected. By our third try, we had it down pat. "
"The only thing that held us up was a lot of joking about who would control "
"which body part. Mei-Yin patently refused to switch off of the sword arm and "
"Helena was convinced that she'd trip us if she took the legs.\n"
"\n"
"I know it goes against my principles as an engineer, but after that, I think "
"I'm actually excited to pilot this thing. Purity be damned."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/3456531488"
msgid ""
"With the hearts or minds of his three lieutenants in hand, you must travel "
"across the wastes and walk the forbidden plains - into the heart of the "
"barren garden. It's here where his power is strongest, but he will show "
"himself nowhere else. He has no reason to step down from his throne.\n"
"\n"
"Yet in this place, if you call him with the voices of his lessers, then he "
"will come. With all the might and hatred of the violet poison from which he "
"was born, he will answer your call:\n"
"\n"
"The King of Shadows. The King of Death.\n"
"\n"
"Do not summon him recklessly. Before you challenge him, you'll need to "
"prepare. As it happens, this is one thing I can help you with."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4117262098"
msgid ""
"Without Ao Yue, we had to move cautiously. Another battle with the demons "
"could prove fatal, but we managed to avoid their sight. All that was left was "
"the climb.\n"
"With no mount, we had to use climbing picks to slowly make our way upwards. "
"It was a long and treacherous ascent, and we both nearly fell several times. "
"Fortunately, we were there to catch and support each other, and through our "
"combined strength, we safely reached the caverns above.\n"
"After the climb, we lay there for a long time. I cannot remember if we "
"laughed or cried. Perhaps both. Juzi says that the item she found could help "
"the entire village, but I do not care. I am just so glad we are both still "
"alive."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/850129826"
msgid ""
"Without question, it was Hathor's divine will that sent me here, not only so "
"I could spread her joy and compassion, but so I could understand her love. "
"\n"
"\n"
"I thought I knew it before. I loved my family, I loved my fellow priestesses, "
"and I love all those under my care here in Nosti. Yet only when I finally "
"surrendered myself to it, when I let it rush over my body and carry me like "
"the current of a great river did I truly understand it. Only now can I claim "
"to embody Hathor's teachings, thanks to John Dahkeya, this warrior from a "
"distant time and place.\n"
"\n"
"And now, together, we can turn this desert into a paradise."
msgstr ""

