msgctxt "Content/2885459817"
msgid ""
"Working in the dirt was what I was born to do, at least according to my "
"engrammatic aptitude test.\n"
"\n"
"An artificial intelligence weighed my soul and decided it saw a future soil "
"scientist.\n"
" I do have to grudgingly admit I'm good at my day job, but my real passion is "
"coding convincingly randomized events and reactive social intelligence "
"simulations.\n"
"\n"
"So that's what I'm tinkering with when I'm not feeding soil probe samples "
"into a chromatograph.\n"
"\n"
"I know, I know-my work to confirm nutrient transport and healthy geochemical "
"cycling by microbial soil communities is an important part of maintaining "
"this vital biological archive of ours.\n"
"\n"
"The fate of humanity depends on our success, bla bla bla.\n"
"\n"
"It's just that I envy having the kind of freedom people seemed to have in the "
"past to follow their dreams, at least according to our library of historical "
"media."
msgstr ""

