msgctxt "Content/1236700513"
msgid ""
"Yes! Hell yeah! They actually started! They're still pretty banged up, even "
"with the repairs, but both of the abandoned MEKs are operational. Now we've "
"just got to fuse all four of them together.\n"
"\n"
"We've got time to spare too. Our guest of honor is still a ways off. He's "
"slowly lumbering towards us, like it's inevitable that we're going to roll "
"over and die for him. Well guess what, asshole? The only thing that's gonna "
"roll here is that nasty looking head of yours.\n"
"\n"
"Man, my blood is pumping just thinking about it, but I'd better rein it in. "
"When that thing gets here, I'm going to need every ounce of adrenaline I've "
"got."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1273502317"
msgid ""
"Yes, I understand now! All of this is by design. This place, these creatures, "
"our arrival...he orchestrated it all as a test. This artifact isn't the "
"prize, it is simply a token, proof that I am worthy! It is the key that will "
"unlock the path below, and at its end I will find the king. There I will find "
"the Master.\n"
"\n"
"Although if this is the key, then where is the door? That terminal we passed "
"by earlier? Yes, that must be it. I need only convince the others to head in "
"that direction, and then... \n"
"\n"
"It is as I said before, sacrifices must be made. That is the way of things. "
"That is the way of the Master."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1341598498"
msgid "Yes, that’s it... I’m proud of you, Survivor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/1466703152"
msgid ""
"Yes, yes of course! The Edmundium is the cause! If there are truly molten "
"pools of Edmundium somewhere in these caverns, then Edmundium minerals would "
"have spread throughout the soil over time, allowing its wondrous properties "
"to affect nearby flora and fauna.\n"
"Even if it is not the direct source of the charge found in this forest's "
"bioluminescent wildlife, it may have incited incremental changes in those "
"species over several generations, which then led to their development of an "
"internal charge. \n"
"\n"
"How invigorating! I could be standing in the middle of an entire ecosystem "
"that has been absorbing the effects of Edmundium for generations, and all of "
"its secrets are mine for the taking. Magnificent!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/509740005"
msgid ""
"Yesterday, I realized that I could rest no longer. I had no more spare cloth "
"for bandages and had eaten nearly all the moss nearby. Rather than risk the "
"heat of the sun on the surface, I ventured deeper into the caverns.\n"
"It was a treacherous descent, but I am glad I went. This cave is larger than "
"I could have imagined. In fact, it is hardly a cave at all. A great forest "
"flourishes down here. It is as if this whole land is backwards.\n"
"However, there is one thing that is familiar to me. The air is thick with the "
"sound and smell of wild beasts. I must remain on my guard."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Content/4065043594"
msgid ""
"Yesterday, I stalked a giant shelled beast, with large claws that it could "
"use like hands. Though slow, it seemed strong. I decided it would be a good "
"addition to my army, but before I could attempt to bring it down, something "
"swooped down from the sky to attack it.\n"
"It was a great lizard, but not one like the ones I had seen before. No, this "
"beast was a true dragon, long of body with a feathery mane. It used the "
"feathers on its arms to ride the wind and tore its prey's shell asunder with "
"iron claws. When it was finished with its meal, it scaled the cavern wall and "
"became one with the shadows, vanishing entirely from my sight.\n"
"I have found my new prey. Soon, I shall command the might of a dragon."
msgstr ""

