msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3663497630"
msgid "Common"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/1389594039"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Archelon\n"
"Species: Archelon Physicorum\n"
"Time: Late Cretaceous \n"
"Diet: Cnidaria\n"
"Temperament: Docile\n"
"\n"
"Wild \n"
"Archelon Physicorum is a kinder denizen of the deep. With a massive and thick "
"carapace, Archelon survives exclusively on a diet of Cnidaria. These giants "
"are often found in a group with at least one additional specimen, deep in the "
"Islands waters.\n"
"Most Likely due to their diet, Archelon are immune to the effects of torpor "
"and tranquilization. Luckily, taming an Archelon can be done by hand, and "
"only requires a hefty amount of time and biotoxin...\n"
"... lots and lots of biotoxin.\n"
"archelon appear to possess the ability to gain unprecedented amounts of "
"strength when they consume their favorite prey. Once they devour the corpse "
"of a Cnidaria, Archelon have shown an increased resistance to damage, and a "
"tremendous increase in their own attacks.\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"Once they've had their fill of biotoxin, Archelon show great promise as "
"undersea mounts. While they maintain their additional perks consuming "
"Cnidaria, Archelon also produce an amazing algae that herbivorous creatures "
"seem to LOVE! On top of all this, Archelon can seat and additional 4 "
"survivors atop their saddles while also providing oxygen! I would consider it "
"foolish for a tribe to not have at least one Archelon available to them."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/2976659729"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Armadoggo\n"
"Species: Canis fodiensocius\n"
"Time: Late Anthropocene\n"
"Diet: Omnivore (but prefers meat)\n"
"Temperament: Bestest!\n"
"\n"
"Wild\n"
"I’m told this clever canine was commonly sighted in areas contaminated by "
"Element a few centuries after my time, so it may be one of the few lifeforms "
"to have survived the collapse of the ecosphere. Like the dogs of my day, this "
"is a social animal that hunts smaller prey in packs.\n"
"\n"
"That bony, scaled shell likely protects Armadoggo from radiation while also "
"allowing it to burrow through the ground. It can cross long distances "
"tunneling under the surface to avoid larger threats. It doesn’t seem "
"threatened by us, and is in fact unusually curious about "
"humans.\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"Armadoggo seems happier once tamed and eager to help, much like its pampered "
"cousins from my time. And it’s one fiercely protective pet, alerting you to "
"nearby dangers and even keeping some at bay.\n"
"\n"
"Armadoggo turns out to have a knack for tracking down valuable technological "
"trinkets hoarded by some of the corrupted local wildlife. Once it picks up "
"the scent from an Element-poisoned kill, it will take you to its hoarded, "
"eminently weaponizable treasure.\n"
"\n"
"No leash training needed -- your loyal new companion will happily carry gear "
"and armaments while never straying too far away. If your Armadoggo gets hurt, "
"it’s smart enough to hide away underground where it can lick its wounds until "
"it can rejoin you. Looking around at the mess we made of the world, I’m not "
"sure we deserve their devotion.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3826022959"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Aureliax\n"
"Species: Draconis superbus\n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Carnivore\n"
"Temperament: Proudly Aloof\n"
"\n"
"Overview\n"
"Project Aureliax was an early attempt to engineer an auspicious guardian for "
"Arat Prime, obviously inspired by the legendary dragons of East Asia. These "
"serpentine creatures were given a suite of telekinetic enhancements, "
"including an eerie ability to levitate.\n"
"\n"
"On our first sighting of a Titan rampaging through the post-Cataclysmic world "
"at large, we realized these would-be protectors were overmatched and sealed "
"them away with us under the Great Dome. But lately I find myself re-"
"evaluating the usefulness of Aureliax as airpower for our military "
"forces.\n"
"\n"
"Applications\n"
"Earning the trust of one of these supercilious serpents is a challenge... A "
"Thrall must bring gifts to an Aureliax in order to prove their worth. Once "
"satisfied with its tribute, the dragon will coil itself into an ovoid "
"chrysalis to begin the imprinting process. This temporarily helpless egg-"
"shaped bundle must be defended until it ‘hatches’ a newly-bonded "
"Aureliax.\n"
"\n"
"An Aureliax can carry multiple beasts of burden in its airborne coils and "
"protect them with an array of celestial powers. Depending on their mood, they "
"might breathe life or death, locally warp reality to help or hinder flying "
"creatures, or raise icy pillars and spikes to throw allies or stab "
"enemies.\n"
"\n"
"While not the most intimidating creature in our menagerie, an Aureliax is the "
"envy of the earthbound.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/136233018"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Aureliax\n"
"Species: Draconis superbus\n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Carnivore\n"
"Temperament: Proudly Aloof\n"
