msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3773852531"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Bison\n"
"Species: Bison matrislac\n"
"Time: Early Pleistocene\n"
"Diet: Herbivore\n"
"Temperament: Territorial\n"
"\n"
"Wild\n"
"After dealing with the endless parade of mutants and freaks on the ARKs, it "
"might feel like a pleasant surprise to run across some ordinary-looking "
"buffalo! Just make sure to enjoy the local bison at a distance, if you’ve "
"brought along anything as big as an allosaur -- they become aggressively "
"territorial around larger predators.\n"
"\n"
"Once provoked, you can expect these stubborn slabs of meat to fight until the "
"bitter end. An agitated bison will throw that massive weight around to defend "
"its herd even when overmatched. I watched one knock a rex senseless before "
"tossing the dazed would-be predator off a cliff!\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"Breaking one of these overstuffed bovines is tougher than you might think... "
"All that extra bulk makes bison especially tough to knock out. These loveable "
"meatballs are worth taming, because they’ll fight for you as fiercely as "
"their own herd. Your bison may not end fights quickly, but it will take a "
"beating and tussle with just about any threat.\n"
"\n"
"A tame mama bison will prove to be a useful dairy animal for your tribe, as "
"long as she’s nursing. That milk is extremely nutritious and actually pairs "
"well with some of the more interesting recipes Survivors have concocted. Any "
"nearby baby creature will want some, once they smell it… Heck, even baby "
"wyverns treat it like their mother’s milk!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3937404796"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Cat\n"
"Species: Felis catus\n"
"Time: Holocene\n"
"Diet: Carnivore\n"
"Temperament: Cat\n"
"\n"
"Wild\n"
"Why am I not surprised that common house cats survived the end of the world? "
"Feral cats have always been reasonably good at avoiding wild predators… Maybe "
"it’s more of a wonder they haven’t managed to wreck the ecosystem here, given "
"their taste for the feathered dinosaur descendants of my day.\n"
"\n"
"Cats are unpredictable little goblins. Some attack anyone who invades their "
"personal space, some run and hide, and a few are actually friendly. But the "
"really mean cats will cling onto you while trying to scratch your eyes out. "
"You’ll need to slap those off your face while you still have "
"one.\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"These fuzzy little fiends are fickle friends, but I’d bet you could win one "
"over with a bit of meat or fish and some stroking of its malicious little "
"ego. Not sure why you’d want to do that, exactly… Maybe they’d help keep "
"thieving vermin from your camp? Or you could try drying out their spit-up "
"hairballs for insulation…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/4104233735"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Ceratosaurus \n"
"Species: Ceratosaurus Punctura \n"
"Time: Late Jurassic \n"
"Diet: Carnivore \n"
"Termperament: Extremely Aggressive \n"
"\n"
"While I'm surprised I haven't encountered them sooner, I'd rather them just "
"vanish all-together. Ceratosaurus is as rughtless as they are quick. While "
"not the most damaging carnivores you'll encounter, they are certainly some of "
"the most persistent. I've seen these creatures even exhibit a sort of ... "
"stalking behavior unlike anything else I've seen on The Island. While they "
"may not make themselves known to you immediately, they certainly know where "
"YOU are! \n"
"\n"
"The spines on Ceratosaurus have a very unique and powerful trait: Venom! This "
"hemotoxin has the bizarre reaction with blood, making it incredibly "
"nutritious to carnivores. The more intense the venom infection, the more "
"beneficial the blood becomes. I've witnessed tribes that have managed to tame "
"these beasts use it to great effect against larger threats, and even The "
"Islands guardians! Perhaps this desire to devour envenomed prey can be used "
"against them...?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/194739721"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Cryolophosaurus\n"
"Species: Cryolophosaurus Glacialis\n"
"Time: Early Jurassic\n"
"Diet: Carnivore\n"
"Temperament: Extremely Aggressive\n"
"\n"
"Wild\n"
"For its small and seemingly innocent stature, Cryolophosaurus is one of the "
"most dangerous creatures I've encountered on the ark. Cryo seems to possess a "
"unique gular pouch that houses a potent freezing and tranquilizing agent. By "
"intaking water or snow in its native habitat, Cryo can store this liquid and "
"use it to \n"
"devastating effect; as tranquilizing spit, or a freezing gust of air. When "
"subduing targets in this manner, Cryo seems to enter a hyper state displayed "
"by vibrant flashing patterns and hyperventilating. This frenzied energy gives "
"Cryo a significant boost in speed and power, which makes avoiding these "
"debilitating attacks all the more crucial. Although they excel at "
"tranquilizing targets, they themselves are not immune to the effects of "
"torpor. While traditional methods will work but return weaker results, a well-"
"armored survivor with shield in hand, is quite successful at giving a Cryo a "
"taste of its' own cold \n"
"medicine.\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"Tamed Cryolophosaurus are one of the most successful taming partners you "
"could find, with torpor attacks that can cause even some of the strongest "
"creatures to succumb to sleep. Its' freezing breath, while potent on enemies, "
"also boasts a useful secondary benefit to allies. With a careful coating of "
"this icy substance, allies will gain an icy coat of armor to help stave off "
"damage. When hyper, Cryo can also assist in the chase by slowing down running "
"targets with their chilling bites. While not quite able to stand as a "
"powerhouse on its' own, Cryolophosaurus make for an excellent debilitating "
"and status applying beast. As long as you're not afraid to get a little cold "
"or sleepy..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/1839555793"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Deinosuchus\n"
"Species: Deinosuchus Sanguineus \n"
"Time: Late Cretaceous \n"
"Diet: Carnivore \n"
"Temperament: Aggressive \n"
"\n"
"I believed Sarcosuchus was the largest crocodilian on The Island, until I "
"encountered Deinosuchus. Massive and bulky, this specimen seems to actually "
"be a mix of its' namesake, and a similar species known as Purussaurus. "
"\n"
"\n"
"Deionosuchus sport huge and powerful jaws, wich they utilize to break the "
"bones of their prey, and halt their escape. Attempting to escape while "
"suffering the effects of their bite can lead to your demise. This coupled "
"with their incredibly tough hide can make disposing of Deinosuchus a "
"difficult and dangerous task.\n"
"\n"
"When tamed, Deinosuchus can make quick work of many creatures, both land and "
"water. Most creatures seem to lack the intelligence to halt their movement "
"when suffering the desctructive effects of a Deinosuchus bite, and this "
"ultimately costs them their life. Any tribe in control of a  Deinosuchus "
"packs a dangerous punch... or in this case... bite!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/1731631716"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Deinotherium\n"
"Species: Deinotherium Colossus\n"
"Time: Late Miocene\n"
"Diet: Herbivore\n"
"Temperament: Territorial\n"
"\n"
"Wild \n"
"Colossus felt like an appropriate name for such a massive variant of the "
"already large elephant. Deinotherium dwarf their Mammoth cousins, and "
"demonstrate terrifying strength and speed. You do not want to upset one of "
"these! When angered, Deinotherium instead take an aggressive stance which "
"results in a charge if the foe lingers for longer than welcome. In their "
"hierachical based herds, aggrivated Deinotheriums will rally eachother with "
"powerful roars. If you want to pick a fight with a herd, you should be "
"ready.\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"Deinotherium are no easy feat to tame. During the aggressive posture they "
"exhibit, Deinotherium will show various signals to indicate whether they're "
"bluffing in their attack or just want that tasty beer they smell! Once tamed, "
"these terrible bests will handily tear down opposing structures and forces, "
"as well as providing some powerful moral boosting calls!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/2689608362"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Drakelings\n"
"Species: Draco temporanima\n"
"Time: Unknown\n"
"Diet: Carnivore (Prefers Cooked)\n"
"Temperament: Curious\n"
"\n"
"Wild\n"
"I must be adapting to my weird new life on these ARKs, because I wasn’t even "
"surprised to run across a new type of dragon. Despite its smaller stature, "
"this friendly little fella seems more like the four-legged guardian of the "
"Island than its bipedal wyvern cousins.\n"
"\n"
"Since all four varieties of Drakeling seem to be able to interbreed, I’ve "
"decided they must all belong to the same species. Each type seems attuned to "
"its own climate, making it tempting for survivors to sort them by the seasons "
"we remember on Earth.\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"Drakelings are drawn to our fires, and curious about people. Show one a bit "
"of kindness and attention, and you’ll gain a powerful -- and portable -- new "
"apprentice. These clever critters seem eager to learn, and to share their "
"knowledge in turn. Let a Drakeling teach your other pets, and in return it "
"will lead you to its hoarded treasure! \n"
"\n"
"Though all Drakelings can act like a reserve parachute, each seasonal variety "
"also has its own powerful breath-attack and special gift. A spring Drakeling "
"will invigorate you, while the summer variety will keep you moving. The "
"autumnal breed empowers you and increases your harvest yields, while the "
"wintery type insulates and cushions you from damage.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/1309002674"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Gigadesmodus\n"
"Species: Gigadesmodus regius\n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Carnivore\n"
"Temperament: Ruthlessly Aggressive\n"
"\n"
"Overview\n"
"Our gene-forges have at long last delivered a singular regal mount worthy of "
"my esteem! Gigadesmodus is a truly intimidating chiropteran steed "
"unparalleled in history or legend. This mighty colossus will earn the respect "
"and awe of all who see it winging across the skies above our "
"kingdom.\n"
"\n"
"Applications\n"
"In war-readiness, Gigadesmodus surpasses every measure. That fearsome "
"strength means it can easily carry my mobile command center on its back while "
"hauling any behemoth high above a battlefield. Echolocation allows "
"Gigadesmodus to navigate in complete darkness, and its nocturnal aggression "
"fuels a relentless pursuit of my enemies. \n"
"\n"
"If any challenge to my authority were to arise, they would have little hope "
"of overcoming the ferocious creature’s combat prowess. I’ve altered the "
"metabolism of Gigadesmodus to promote rapid healing with every bite it "
"delivers, and to share its regenerative power with me.\n"
"\n"
"Gigadesmodus carries a reservoir of consumed blood mixed with Red Element "
"that can deal with my enemies at a significant distance. And in the event an "
"example must be made, the beast’s sharp tail can be employed to deliver a "
"devastating finishing blow.\n"
"\n"
"I am truly delighted with this living emblem of my enduring majesty! Long "
"shall we reign.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3537994551"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Gloon\n"
"Species: Microluminis pupulis \n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Carnivore\n"
"Temperament: Repellant\n"
"\n"
"Overview\n"
"Our kingdom's perimeter is plagued by the fever dreams of a mad wizard! "
"Consider this floating little freak, the ‘Gloon,’ as my Thralls have named "
"it. I refuse to speak the word again. They are, to me, Oddities. Edmund "
"Rockwell must have fashioned these repulsive balloon animals to function like "
"the charge-absorbing pets Helena Walker was able to tame, aboard the ARK that "
"eventually delivered her old friend to our doorstep. I very much doubt the "
"potential utility of such an Oddity can outshine its "
"absurdity.\n"
"\n"
"Applications\n"
"In her archived field notes from that malfunctioning orbital arcology, Walker "
"described the ability of bioluminous creatures to attract or repel various "
"cavern-dwelling mutants. These Oddities seem similarly capable of "
"manipulating the invasive creatures at our borders, but I am loath to "
"tolerate their use as living so-called ‘charge lanterns’. LLike their clever "
"but cowardly master, Rockwell’s gifts tend to come with a curse.\n"
"\n"
"The pupils of the Oddities can widen or contract to flood an area with "
"charged light or focus it into destructive lasers. It can also wriggle those "
"same glowing spots across its bulbous eye-sacs to mesmerize the weak-minded. "
"Most annoyingly, the Oddities can warp light around themselves to effectively "
"become invisible.\n"
"\n"
"As if their ocular abilities weren’t confounding enough, the bilious spit of "
"these floating gaslights seems to enrage any nearby aberrations. Although my "
"Thralls have learned to isolate and tame the little Oddities by destroying "
"their attendant revenants, I have expressly forbidden their use within our "
"city limits. I think I may decree summary execution for any of my subjects "
"who dares call them a ‘Gloon’ henceforth. Damn."
msgstr ""

