msgctxt "GraphLiteral/872370676"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Helicoprion\n"
"Species: Helicoprion Frendo\n"
"Time: Early Permian \n"
"Diet: Soft bodied prey\n"
"Temperament: Relaxed\n"
"\n"
"Wild \n"
"Similar in size to Megaladon but far more calm, Helicoprion reclusively lurk "
"in the open waters of the Arks ocean environments. While they are imposing "
"with their familiar silhouette, Helicoprion pose no threat unless provvoked. "
"That is, unless you happen to be an unfortunate ammonite, which Helicoprion "
"have a strong desire to chomp down on!\n"
"\n"
"With strong jaws and an evven stronger tail, Helicoprion can pose a dangerous "
"threat if they'e been bothered. The jaws of Helicoprion are used to quickly "
"and efficiently slice up the soft bodies of cephalopod creatures, and the "
"tail in particular has evolvved to be more like a Thresher sharks. This "
"significant change is used to great effect at stunning prey. Some survviving "
"claim more powerful Heli can evven knock out foes with a powerful whip of "
"their tail!\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"The truly remarkable jaw of Helicoprion can be used for much more than just "
"eating Ammonites. Oddly enough, the precise cutting power the tooth whorl "
"provvides can be used to seperate the various components of equipment. For "
"some older specimens, this process allows survivors to record the crafting "
"requirements for their various equipment. I've only seen the most experienced "
"crafters employ this bizarre utility, but it's an astonishingly useful one "
"for sure!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/4125880044"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Malwyn\n"
"Species: Vulpes daemonicus \n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Omnivore\n"
"Temperament: Cold-heartedly Tenacious\n"
"\n"
"Overview\n"
"It took several decades longer than expected, but at last we have achieved a "
"breakthrough in the artificial hyper-evolution of our Veilwyn familiars into "
"more imposing creatures. Red Element will fuse with Vulpite to create a new "
"amalgam we call Sanguine Vulpite. And introducing Sanguine Vulpite into the "
"system of a young Veilwyn will result in a most fearsome and regal mount. "
"Let’s call it a Malwyn.\n"
"\n"
"Applications\n"
"Here is a creature with a single-minded focus on threat elimination. Unlike "
"its more benevolent cousin, the Solwyn, a Malwyn has no interest in safe "
"exploration or play. It will instead identify prey, focus all its terrible "
"malice onto that unlucky target, and attack. With its enhanced teleabsorptive "
"abilities, a Malwyn can slow regenerative processes, induce sluggishness, and "
"create frailty where none existed before.\n"
"\n"
"While its climbing prowess is a disappointment compared to the Solwyn breed, "
"a Malwyn will more readily use its teleportational ability to pounce on its "
"prey across great distances. Some of my Thralls have complained about the "
"prolonged deactivation period of the Malwyn’s portals. Those who do are "
"unworthy of one of these austere mounts. The ruthless efficiency of this "
"majestic creature makes it the ideal beast to lead a hunting party.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/2550034649"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Megaraptor\n"
"Species: Megaraptor Sceleratus\n"
"Time: Late Cretaceous\n"
"Diet: Carnivore\n"
"Temperament: Solitary Aggressive\n"
"\n"
"Wild\n"
"Trust me, you don't want one of these creepy killers hunting you. Megaraptor "
"picks off its civtims one at a time, like the villain in an old-school "
"slasher flick. And once you've been targeted, your stalker will scare away "
"your friends and allies with its unnerving glare.\n"
"\n"
"You won't see this monster coming until it's right on top of you. That's when "
"megaraptor pounces, pinning you down and scattering everyone nearby to leave "
"you defenseless. Talk about a jump scare! The final indignity is that your "
"death will give the beast the strength to shrug off any attempt to avenge "
"you. \n"
"\n"
"DomesticatedBefore you can tame a Megaraptor, you'll have to earn its "
"respect. Find and claim its grisly altar of carcasses, then keep the enraged "
"owner at bay with fire. Just make sure you stay on a constant swivel, because "
"this fiend will fight like hell for its trophies.\n"
"\n"
"Manage to break one of these butchers, and you'll share all the meat from its "
"many kills. You'll also gain an assassin eager to isolate and murder your "
"enemies. But know that Megaraptor hunts alone. Uncomfotable around even its "
"own kind, this army of one will lose its fighting edge around others."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/1685074115"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Oasisaur \n"
"Species: Oasisaur zurzura \n"
"Time: Unknown \n"
"Diet: Herbivore \n"
"Temperament: Friendly \n"
" \n"
"Wild \n"
"Where do I start with Oasisaur zurzura? Like most of the unique wildlife I’ve "
"encountered here, this flying island feels like something from legendary "
"fantasy. It’s as big as a Titanosaur, but somehow it can still defy gravity! "
"\n"
"My hunch is that Oasisaur consumes great bunches of vegetation at once, so a "
"handful of berries wouldn’t be an enticing enough offering. You’d have better "
"luck courting its affection with a topiary or potted shrub, as long as you’re "
"ready to chase rival suitors off the behemoth’s back. \n"
"This roaming oasis carries soil on its back so fertile that anything planted "
"in it will flourish, even if practically ignored. And that back seems like it "
"has room enough for a small neighborhood...  \n"
" \n"
"Domesticated \n"
"This living landmass will nurture its longer-term inhabitants. That "
"friendship is worth the time investment, because favored residents get access "
"to a pool with truly miraculous properties. For starters, its restorative "
"waters will cure bathers of nearly any illness or affliction. \n"
"Most unbelievably, the wellspring of an Oasisaur can reincarnate your lost "
"animal friends! Whether by transcendental magic or access to the mysterious "
"technologies of these ARKs, I’ve seen a fallen pet returned to newborn life "
"by committing their essence to that rejuvenating pool. \n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/2136251779"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Ossidon\n"
"Species: Cryopithecus Dominus\n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Carnivore\n"
"Temperament: Relentless\n"
"\n"
"Overview\n"
"Project Ossidon has already yielded the ideal apex protector for our people! "
"Experimentation with Red Element infusion of creatures engineered for "
"hardiness has given us a truly fearsome anthropoid that can dominate the "
"Antarctic wastes. \n"
"\n"
"Note Information\n"
"By design, these noble snow-beasts can be sorted at a distance by adaption. "
"Each specimen morphologically expresses its most useful genomic trait. The "
"healthiest Ossidon will grow largest, while the deadliest will flash the "
"longest claws.\n"
"\n"
"Applications\n"
"Biotech teams are laboring around the clock to gestate and domesticate as "
"many Ossidons as possible, for the day they may be needed to keep a Titan at "
"bay. In the near term, these glorious behemoths will be employed as our "
"peacekeepers and guardians.\n"
"\n"
"Visual Attachment\n"
"Ossidon was engineered to produce excessive quantities of cryogenic mucus. "
"This foul substance is the creature's greatest weapon, whether rolled into an "
"icy wrecking ball or spit in a shower of bone-chilling slush.\n"
"\n"
"Any rider will feel unstoppable astride one of these imposing brutes! Our "
"mounted forces will soon become as integral to the defense of this outpost as "
"our shielding."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/1298530203"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Solwyn\n"
"Species: Vulpes angelicus \n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Omnivore\n"
"Temperament: Resolutely protective\n"
"\n"
"Overview\n"
"One of our geologists discovered a potentially-exploitable new mineral "
"resource while surveying the perimeter for veins of Element. Some of this "
"novel substance -- which she named ‘Vulpite’ -- was ingested by her mutant "
"companion before she could stop it. Her juvenile Veilwyn underwent an "
"unexpected metamorphosis during its next teleportation, increasing in mass, "
"muscle density, and cognitive response.\n"
"With its strength, speed, and extraordinary abilities enhanced by Vulpite, "
"this once-diminutive pet can now carry a rider across the Antarctic wastes at "
"great speed. We decided to call her majestic new mount a "
"Solwyn.\n"
"\n"
"Applications\n"
"Any young Veilwyn fed enough Vulpite will become a Solwyn. This miraculous "
"fox-mount protects its rider from the ravages of our environment, as they "
"speed together across glacial terrain, up sheer ice cliffs, and through "
"frigid polar waters. \n"
"\n"
"A Solwyn can use its cryokinesis to create fragile ice-bridges or project "
"sharp ice shards. Its ability to generate localized wormholes allows the "
"creature to tuck itself into a quantum hideaway for later retrieval. The "
"Solwyn’s Vulpite-enhanced system gives it greatly increased strength, healing "
"factor, and velocity.\n"
"\n"
"Such uncanny traversal abilities and portability would seem to make the "
"Solywn an ideal mount for scouting applications. Best of all, a Solwyn's "
"drive to protect its bonded Thrall has also expanded, making it more than a "
"match for any modestly-sized threat to its rider.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3068648163"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Thrall\n"
"Species: Homo servilis\n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Sanguinovore\n"
"Temperament: Eternally Obedient\n"
"\n"
"Overview\n"
"Regrettably I must impose a rigid and clear social hierarchy to ensure our "
"ongoing survival. There must be a clear division of status in our kingdom "
"between the citizenry and our vast underclass of worker drones. Still, we "
"must recognize and reward the best of our clones, for the greater good.\n"
"\n"
"We have already had to accept the harsh reality that our labor force must "
"also serve as our food source… But we will need a class of loyal taskmasters "
"to oversee their efforts, while also ensuring they continue to share their "
"precious lifeblood on demand. Perhaps we could make a ceremony of that "
"process, thereby celebrating their contribution to the ongoing survival of "
"our people.\n"
"\n"
"Applications\n"
"Certain of our worker stock have proven themselves loyal and worthy of "
"promotion. These select few thralls can be trusted with a modicum of our "
"bioengineered power to help them maintain order. Supervision of the "
"enthralled can be assured via remote connection with their neural centers, "
"making it possible to assert control of their higher functions if necessary.  "
"While our thralls keep the peace, we can turn our attention to larger threats "
"inside and outside the kingdom.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/1613885087"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Veilwyn\n"
"Species: Vulpes frigus\n"
"Time: Necrocene\n"
"Diet: Omnivore\n"
"Temperament: Affectionately Playful\n"
"\n"
"Overview\n"
"The Turning of our people has gifted us with longevity, great strength, and "
"freedom from starvation. Maintaining the loyalty of our thralls and the "
"obedience of the clones they police for us may require something more than "
"brute intimidation. To this end, I find myself weighing the potential of "
"mutated local wildlife like the Veilwyn. In these early days of our kingdom, "
"an animal companion capable of comforting and protecting our people through "
"the long Antarctic night might also have an inspirational "
"value.\n"
"\n"
"Applications\n"
"This playful vulpine beast has many unlikely but uncannily useful talents. "
"One can't help but admire a Veilwyn's ability to generate localized wormholes "
"through which to summon a pack of friends that will help protect its master. "
"And even in more peaceful times, these seemingly friendly foxes could subdue "
"would-be predators with their cryogenic bite.\n"
"\n"
"I may consider pairing my most trusted servants with Veilwyn companions. "
"Perhaps even a thrall deserves the unwavering fidelity of a valiant familiar. "
"This creature could yet become the symbol of my benevolence that elicits the "
"veneration of my vassals. And in this dark tomorrow, their unwavering "
"devotion could serve to remind us all of the humanity we had to set aside in "
"order to survive.\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/2777881703"
msgid ""
"Common Name: Xiphactinus \n"
"Species: Xiphactinus Velox \n"
"Time: Late Cretaceous \n"
"Diet: Carnivore \n"
"Temperament: Frenzied \n"
"\n"
"Wild \n"
"Xiphactinus Velox is a frighteningly fast creature, lurking in The Islands' "
"oceans. Most often appearing in groups, Xiphactinus can quickly overwhelm "
"its' victims. They have been observed to grab smaller prety in their "
"terrifying jaws and thrash wildly to deplete their engergy. When subdued, "
"they will proceed to swallow the prey whole, something I have witnessed "
"befall many unfortunate survivors. Beware Xiphactinus that have recently fed, "
"as they will become frenzied from the clouds of blood they've created. For "
"targets too large to be swallowed by its horrific maw, Xiphactinus will "
"briefly grab their target and proceed to tear off a chunk of flesh, causing "
"the target to begin bleeding out. On several occassions, I've noticed "
"Xiphactinus will attack other ocean species such as Megalodon, and even "
"larger threats such as Mosasaur! Be glad that you're not their only "
"target!\n"
"\n"
"Tamed\n"
"Xiphactinus make for excellent mounts for exploring the ARK's vast ocean "
"environments. Their powerful jaws can be utilized to grab smaller prey, while "
"leaving a nasty bleeding wound on larger opponents. With good manueverability "
"and a violent nature, any tribes partaking in sea-warfare will be sure to "
"have a shoal of these \"Dire Tuna\"."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3586986707"
msgid ""
"Common name:\n"
"Roll Rat\n"
"Species: Heterocephalus Magnus\n"
"Time: Holocene\n"
"Diet: Herbivore\n"
"Temperament: Passive\n"
"\n"
"Wild\n"
"Bearing a strong resemblance to its relative, the naked mole rat, "
"Heterocephalus magnus is a gentle giant that digs for plants and fungi with "
"its imposing front teeth. While foraging, it often uncovers precious "
"resources inadvertently, but survivors should claim them with caution, as "
"this triggers an aggressive response.\n"
"\n"
"When threatened, Heterocephalus rolls up into a ball to shield itself with "
"the armored plates on its back, much like an armadillo. It then rolls around "
"like an oversized bowling ball, smashing through rocks, walls and hopefully "
"its aggressor.\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"While hardly a ferocious war beast, Heterocephalus is an effective transport "
"that can carry up to three passengers. In theory, it could also be siege "
"weapon, as its rolling attack can dent even metal. Fortunately, most "
"survivors use a special saddle that deploys a protective canopy when it "
"starts spinning, which not only keeps them from getting squished, but "
"provides extra protection to rider and mount alike."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3608260884"
msgid ""
"Common name:\n"
"Tapejara\n"
"Species: Tapejara imperator\n"
"Time: Cretaceous\n"
"Diet: Carnivorous\n"
"Temperament: Skittish\n"
"\n"
"Wild\n"
"Tapejara imperator is a marvel to watch in the wild. It has astonishing "
"agility compared to the Island's other flyers thanks in large part to the "
"rudder-like fin that extends from its snout to the back of its "
"skull.\n"
"\n"
"Initially, I'd thought the fin was simply composed of keratin, but closer "
"inspection has led me to believe that it is actually some kind of sensory "
"organ. Not only does it decrease Tapejara's turning radius even at high "
"speeds, but it apparently provides Tapejara with extra information to help it "
"fly through the air with unparalleled grace. I've even seen Tapejara hover "
"and strafe side-to-side in the air without moving forward at all. It's quite "
"remarkable. The creature also makes effective use of razor-sharp claws to "
"latch onto surfaces such as the trunks of tall trees, holding its position "
"indefinitely.\n"
"\n"
"Domesticated\n"
"Warlike tribes appear to consider Tapejara the equivalent of a versatile "
"rotor aircraft, capable of rapid positional changes and aggressive "
"agility.\n"
"\n"
"When domesticated the Tapejara is typically outfitted with a unique triple-"
"rider saddle, enabling two passengers to wield handheld weaponry while the "
"pilot takes the reins. When the Tapejara is latched onto a surface, both the "
"passengers and pilot are able to make full use of their weapons "
"together!\n"
"\n"
"Evidently what this skittering creature lacks in distance-stamina, "
"constitution, and weight carrying capacity, it makes up for in "
"maneuverability and combat versatility."
msgstr ""

