msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3798513991"
msgid "It was once called ‘Walker’... ‘Helena Walker’."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3584520472"
msgid ""
"It would be hard to strike out alone again in this poisoned wilderness..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/2736229692"
msgid "It {1} Results {0}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/1493575375"
msgid "It's a paradise now, beyond wonder, with all things in balance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/2356035772"
msgid ""
"It's amazing how even in the coldest places, there are still hidden pockets "
"of warmth and beauty... Flowers straining for the light."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/366201347"
msgid ""
"It's been a day of reversals, I guess. I'd slunk off to brood somewhere, and "
"Mei-Yin tracked me down to talk, mostly about a subject we'd been avoiding: "
"Diana. Since she opened my wound, she'd open hers, she said.\n"
"\n"
"It didn't feel like a fair trade. The way she clutches that necklace, and how "
"she smiles when she remembers the woman who gave it to her, there's a "
"gentleness there that she offers to nothing else. To persevere with a wound "
"so deep that it may never heal, her will must be extraordinary, "
"but...\n"
"\n"
"Maybe it helps that we're limping onward together, and maybe as long as we're "
"here to prop each other up, we'll see this through.\n"
"\n"
"In the end, Mei-Yin changed her vote, and the ayes had it. We're following "
"the signal."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3892532502"
msgid "It's nothing more than that. And I'll always love you there."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "GraphLiteral/3908873919"
msgid "It... spoke to me. I finally know what I have to do."
msgstr ""

